WEBVTT

1
00:00:24.524 --> 00:00:26.276
[RUMBLING]

2
00:00:52.678 --> 00:00:54.763
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

3
00:00:57.432 --> 00:01:00.227
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

4
00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:25.502
[PEOPLE CHATTERING IN GERMAN]

5
00:01:35.887 --> 00:01:37.931
[METAL CLATTERS]

6
00:01:48.317 --> 00:01:50.360
[CAR HONKING]

7
00:01:53.697 --> 00:01:55.449
SOLDIER 1 : [IN ENGLISH]
One of our vehicles. is it?

8
00:01:55.532 --> 00:01:57.034
[CAR CONTINUES HONKING]

9
00:01:57.659 --> 00:01:59.119
Move! Move!

10
00:01:59.202 --> 00:02:00.829
SOLDIER 2: Make way! Make way!

11
00:02:02.497 --> 00:02:03.999
[MAN SPEAKING GERMAN]

12
00:02:07.127 --> 00:02:08.754
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

13
00:02:08.837 --> 00:02:10.088
[ENGINE STOPS]

14
00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:17.012
[MAN CONTINUES SPEAKING GERMAN]

15
00:02:24.728 --> 00:02:26.021
[MAN CONTINUES SPEAKING GERMAN]

16
00:02:27.105 --> 00:02:28.940
[MAN CONTINUES SPEAKING GERMAN]

17
00:02:29.441 --> 00:02:30.942
[FABRIC TEARING]

18
00:02:36.573 --> 00:02:39.159
SOLDIER 3: [IN ENGLISH]
Hey! Let me see your hands!

19
00:02:42.871 --> 00:02:45.290
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

20
00:02:46.166 --> 00:02:48.043
[CROWD MURMURING]

21
00:02:51.838 --> 00:02:54.800
[WIND WHOOSHING]

22
00:02:58.678 --> 00:03:00.138
- [CAR DOOR OPENS]
- [SOLDIERS INHALE SHARPLY]

23
00:03:04.059 --> 00:03:05.977
Jesus Christ. that's Hermann Göring.

24
00:03:06.061 --> 00:03:08.063
- Who?
- SOLDIER 3: Hitler's second-in-command.

25
00:03:09.314 --> 00:03:10.399
The <i>Führer</i>-in-waiting.

26
00:03:11.233 --> 00:03:12.526
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

27
00:03:22.411 --> 00:03:23.412
[IN ENGLISH] What did he say?

28
00:03:24.913 --> 00:03:26.998
He asked us to get his luggage.

29
00:03:29.501 --> 00:03:31.503
- [THUNDER RUMBLING]
- [RAIN PATTERING]

30
00:03:43.515 --> 00:03:45.392
[BANGING ON DOOR]

31
00:03:47.185 --> 00:03:48.270
MAN: Justice Jackson?

32
00:03:49.354 --> 00:03:51.022
That depends on if you have a good reason

33
00:03:51.106 --> 00:03:53.191
to be banging on my door
at 3:00 in the morning.

34
00:03:53.275 --> 00:03:54.985
MAN: They captured Hermann Göring alive.

35
00:03:57.195 --> 00:03:58.530
- Where?
- Austria.

36
00:04:01.324 --> 00:04:02.409
What are they gonna do with him?

37
00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:04.828
MAN: Well. that's the real question.
isn't it? Can I come in?

38
00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:06.872
- No.
- But it's raining.

39
00:04:06.955 --> 00:04:09.583
I can see that. Are they gonna shoot him?

40
00:04:09.666 --> 00:04:10.792
MAN: Not that I know of.

41
00:04:12.085 --> 00:04:13.879
Well. for a long time.
they were gonna shoot him.

42
00:04:13.962 --> 00:04:14.963
MAN: Yes. sir.

43
00:04:15.046 --> 00:04:16.923
Churchill and Roosevelt
signed the order themselves.

44
00:04:17.007 --> 00:04:18.133
An order you opposed.

45
00:04:18.216 --> 00:04:19.759
I'm a Supreme Court Justice.

46
00:04:19.843 --> 00:04:22.345
I tend to frown on executing men
without a trial.

47
00:04:22.429 --> 00:04:23.972
That's what I'm here to talk about.

48
00:04:26.224 --> 00:04:27.225
WOMAN: <i>It can't be done.</i>

49
00:04:27.309 --> 00:04:29.811
- JACKSON: You keep saying that.
- Because it can't be done.

50
00:04:29.895 --> 00:04:31.188
Give me one good reason why not.

51
00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:33.523
There's no legal precedent for a trial.

52
00:04:34.774 --> 00:04:37.194
There's no international law
to base the charges on.

53
00:04:37.277 --> 00:04:41.281
No one has ever tried war criminals
outside of one nation's jurisdiction

54
00:04:41.364 --> 00:04:44.117
because the whole concept
of international law is that

55
00:04:44.201 --> 00:04:47.287
one country can't tell another country's
citizens how to conduct themselves.

56
00:04:47.370 --> 00:04:49.247
- Elsie...
- Trying these men

57
00:04:49.331 --> 00:04:51.041
in a German court would be different.

58
00:04:51.124 --> 00:04:53.001
But what you're talking about
is trying them

59
00:04:53.084 --> 00:04:55.504
in some sort of legal limbo
that doesn't exist.

60
00:04:55.587 --> 00:04:57.881
using case law
that hasn't been written yet.

61
00:04:57.964 --> 00:05:00.133
and on the off chance
that you're not keeping track.

62
00:05:00.217 --> 00:05:02.052
that's about four good reasons why not.

63
00:05:02.135 --> 00:05:04.638
- I'm getting you a drink.
- [CHUCKLES] I don't want a drink.

64
00:05:04.721 --> 00:05:07.057
Then I'm getting me another
and getting you one for show.

65
00:05:08.099 --> 00:05:09.351
Who do you put on trial?

66
00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:12.646
The German commanders?

67
00:05:13.396 --> 00:05:14.856
Enlisted men?

68
00:05:14.940 --> 00:05:17.275
What about the judges
who enforced the racial codes?

69
00:05:17.359 --> 00:05:19.152
Obviously. we'd have to work that out.

70
00:05:19.236 --> 00:05:22.989
And once you decide who to put on trial.
what do you charge them with?

71
00:05:23.949 --> 00:05:26.743
Conspiracy to wage
aggressive war on the world.

72
00:05:26.826 --> 00:05:30.830
And you want the United States
to argue that as the prosecution?

73
00:05:30.914 --> 00:05:32.249
I do.

74
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:34.000
ELSIE: Against Germany.

75
00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:36.503
a country that never attacked us.

76
00:05:38.129 --> 00:05:39.130
[SIGHS]

77
00:05:39.631 --> 00:05:42.008
- Say. just for a second. it could be done.
- Robert...

78
00:05:42.092 --> 00:05:43.426
Don't you wanna know how I'd do it?

79
00:05:44.844 --> 00:05:48.848
It would have to be
a completely international effort.

80
00:05:50.892 --> 00:05:53.645
<i>All of the Allies
would have to participate.</i>

81
00:05:53.728 --> 00:05:54.813
<i>The U.S..</i>

82
00:05:54.896 --> 00:05:57.649
<i>Britain. France. Russia.</i>

83
00:05:57.732 --> 00:06:00.026
<i>You can't do it without the Russians.</i>

84
00:06:00.110 --> 00:06:02.404
<i>Four international judges.</i>

85
00:06:02.487 --> 00:06:04.322
ELSIE: <i>You're talking about a tribunal.</i>

86
00:06:04.406 --> 00:06:05.407
JACKSON: <i>Exactly.</i>

87
00:06:05.949 --> 00:06:08.743
<i>The world needs to know
what these men did.</i>

88
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:10.829
It's a logistical nightmare.

89
00:06:10.912 --> 00:06:11.913
I know.

90
00:06:14.082 --> 00:06:15.709
But it has to be done.

91
00:06:16.459 --> 00:06:18.712
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:06:23.508 --> 00:06:25.552
[TRAIN WHISTLING]

93
00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:48.074
Pick a card.

94
00:06:50.243 --> 00:06:51.244
I don't think so.

95
00:06:56.207 --> 00:06:57.417
Ask me to pick one.

96
00:07:08.136 --> 00:07:09.137
Pick a card.

97
00:07:16.770 --> 00:07:19.606
Now ask me to please remember it
and put it back in the deck.

98
00:07:20.982 --> 00:07:23.818
Please remember it
and put it back in the deck.

99
00:07:27.864 --> 00:07:29.115
Now shuffle 'em.

100
00:07:39.709 --> 00:07:40.919
Now what?

101
00:07:41.002 --> 00:07:42.671
My card was the three of spades.

102
00:07:42.754 --> 00:07:43.963
Well. that's hardly a trick.

103
00:07:44.047 --> 00:07:45.173
Turn over the top one.

104
00:07:52.764 --> 00:07:54.641
[CHUCKLING]

105
00:07:58.436 --> 00:07:59.437
Who are you?

106
00:08:00.563 --> 00:08:01.690
I'm a psychiatrist.

107
00:08:01.773 --> 00:08:02.816
[CHUCKLES]

108
00:08:04.025 --> 00:08:06.361
Oh. and why are you going to Mondorf?

109
00:08:06.444 --> 00:08:07.487
MAN: I wish I knew.

110
00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:11.157
They send psychiatrists
on secret missions now?

111
00:08:11.241 --> 00:08:12.992
I'm pretty sure I'm the first.

112
00:08:17.455 --> 00:08:20.500
How did you do that? With the cards.

113
00:08:21.418 --> 00:08:22.711
I didn't do anything.

114
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:26.631
You're a really good magician.

115
00:08:30.218 --> 00:08:32.262
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

116
00:08:32.345 --> 00:08:34.764
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

117
00:08:40.687 --> 00:08:42.188
Dr. Kelley?

118
00:08:42.272 --> 00:08:43.940
Sergeant Howie Triest. at your service.

119
00:08:44.023 --> 00:08:46.317
I'm gonna run you over
to the commandant's office.

120
00:08:46.401 --> 00:08:48.111
- Tigers. huh?
- Yes. sir.

121
00:08:48.194 --> 00:08:49.654
Perhaps I'll see you around.

122
00:08:52.323 --> 00:08:53.324
Jiminy.

123
00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:55.744
Who was that?

124
00:08:55.827 --> 00:08:58.037
That. Howie. was a very attractive woman.

125
00:08:58.121 --> 00:09:00.206
- [HOWIE SCOFFS]
- Did you say "commandant"?

126
00:09:01.374 --> 00:09:02.542
Uh. yes. sir. Colonel Andrus.

127
00:09:03.918 --> 00:09:06.337
So. can you tell me
what I'm supposed to be doing here?

128
00:09:06.421 --> 00:09:08.047
I thought the war was over.

129
00:09:09.048 --> 00:09:10.258
I couldn't say.

130
00:09:11.259 --> 00:09:12.677
Couldn't say because you don't know

131
00:09:12.761 --> 00:09:14.846
or you couldn't say 'cause somebody
told you you couldn't say?

132
00:09:16.473 --> 00:09:17.766
I couldn't say.

133
00:09:18.349 --> 00:09:19.434
DOUGLAS: Hmm.

134
00:09:20.101 --> 00:09:22.270
Don't get sore at me. Doc.
I'm just your translator.

135
00:09:23.104 --> 00:09:24.355
Translator for what?

136
00:09:26.024 --> 00:09:28.067
- You'll see.
- [ENGINE REVS]

137
00:09:34.657 --> 00:09:37.660
ANDRUS: <i>Dr. Kelley. apparently.
Central Command thinks</i>

138
00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:39.996
<i>you're some kind of hotshot headshrinker.</i>

139
00:09:40.079 --> 00:09:41.831
<i>I imagine you have some questions for me.</i>

140
00:09:41.915 --> 00:09:43.917
- More than a few.
- Then let's get to it.

141
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.795
You are standing inside
a secret military prison.

142
00:09:46.878 --> 00:09:49.672
It currently houses what's left
of the Nazi High Command.

143
00:09:49.756 --> 00:09:53.551
The governments of Russia. France.
Great Britain. and our United States

144
00:09:53.635 --> 00:09:57.514
are deciding right now whether to put
these men on trial for their lives.

145
00:09:57.597 --> 00:10:00.767
You have been brought in
to inspect and ensure

146
00:10:00.850 --> 00:10:03.812
the prisoners' mental health
should that trial go forward.

147
00:10:04.395 --> 00:10:05.730
Suicide.

148
00:10:05.814 --> 00:10:08.233
That'll be the main concern
with most of the prisoners.

149
00:10:08.316 --> 00:10:11.778
Hitler. Goebbels. and Himmler
have already taken their own lives.

150
00:10:11.861 --> 00:10:13.655
We cannot afford any more losses.

151
00:10:14.823 --> 00:10:16.699
Goebbels and Himmler did it with this.

152
00:10:17.992 --> 00:10:19.577
Hidden cyanide capsule.

153
00:10:20.537 --> 00:10:22.455
The one you'll have to watch
the closest is Göring.

154
00:10:23.039 --> 00:10:24.040
Göring?

155
00:10:25.208 --> 00:10:26.251
As in Hermann Göring?

156
00:10:26.334 --> 00:10:27.418
That's the one.

157
00:10:28.503 --> 00:10:29.587
Hermann Göring's here?

158
00:10:30.338 --> 00:10:32.799
Sergeant. is it possible
the major suffered a large blow

159
00:10:32.882 --> 00:10:34.092
to his head on the way to my office?

160
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.135
- Not that I'm aware of. sir.
- DOUGLAS: Sorry.

161
00:10:36.219 --> 00:10:38.805
- It's just a lot to process.
- Sure it is. Try and do it faster.

162
00:10:38.888 --> 00:10:40.473
- Yes. sir.
- When Göring surrendered.

163
00:10:40.557 --> 00:10:42.433
he was traveling with his family.

164
00:10:42.517 --> 00:10:45.270
He had over a million dollars
in German currency and jewelry.

165
00:10:45.353 --> 00:10:46.896
And a large quantity...

166
00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:48.439
- [CONTAINER CLACKS]
- ...of these.

167
00:10:48.523 --> 00:10:50.775
We had them sent back
to the States for classification.

168
00:10:52.402 --> 00:10:53.403
Paracodeine.

169
00:10:54.028 --> 00:10:56.281
Fairly potent painkiller. I'm a fan.

170
00:10:57.866 --> 00:10:58.950
He says they're for his heart.

171
00:10:59.033 --> 00:11:03.121
Well. then. I have a rather large bridge
in Brooklyn to sell you.

172
00:11:03.204 --> 00:11:05.456
These have nothing to do with the heart.
They're an opiate.

173
00:11:06.499 --> 00:11:08.501
How many pills does he take a day?

174
00:11:08.585 --> 00:11:10.169
- Sergeant?
- Forty. sir.

175
00:11:11.546 --> 00:11:14.591
I think it's safe to say
the <i>Reichsmarschall's</i> got a drug problem.

176
00:11:15.383 --> 00:11:16.467
Where's his family now?

177
00:11:16.551 --> 00:11:18.553
They've been released
and they're not your concern.

178
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:22.390
Your only job is to evaluate
Göring and the others. That is it.

179
00:11:23.516 --> 00:11:24.934
Sir. I'm a good doctor.

180
00:11:25.018 --> 00:11:29.981
but the entire Nazi High Command might be
a little bit beyond my area of expertise.

181
00:11:30.064 --> 00:11:32.567
Believe me. Major. this was not my idea.

182
00:11:34.068 --> 00:11:35.069
Dismissed.

183
00:11:38.948 --> 00:11:41.117
He's not great at pep talks. is he?

184
00:11:41.200 --> 00:11:43.161
Commandant's not known
for his warmth. sir.

185
00:11:43.244 --> 00:11:45.079
- I wanna meet him.
- Who?

186
00:11:45.163 --> 00:11:46.873
- Göring. Right now.
- Excuse me. sir.

187
00:11:46.956 --> 00:11:48.124
You don't wanna get settled first?

188
00:11:48.207 --> 00:11:50.168
I wanna know what I'm dealing with.

189
00:11:50.251 --> 00:11:51.628
All right. well. don't be too intimidated.

190
00:11:51.711 --> 00:11:53.087
I'm not. Tell me about him.

191
00:11:54.005 --> 00:11:57.175
<i>Reichsmarschall</i> Hermann Göring.
President of the <i>Reichstag.</i>

192
00:11:57.258 --> 00:12:00.720
Minister of Aviation.
Commander-in-Chief of the <i>Luftwaffe.</i>

193
00:12:00.803 --> 00:12:04.974
Minister of Economics. a founding member
of the <i>Gestapo</i> secret police.

194
00:12:05.058 --> 00:12:07.477
was appointed Hitler's successor in 1939

195
00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:10.021
and is the highest ranking
German military officer of all time.

196
00:12:10.104 --> 00:12:11.105
Okay.

197
00:12:11.814 --> 00:12:13.733
Now I'm a little intimidated.

198
00:12:13.816 --> 00:12:14.859
Don't be. You're good.

199
00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:18.696
HOWIE: [CLEARS THROAT] <i>Reichsmarschall.</i>

200
00:12:18.780 --> 00:12:20.156
<i>Guten Tag. Herr Triest.</i>

201
00:12:21.449 --> 00:12:22.742
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

202
00:12:23.242 --> 00:12:25.620
[IN ENGLISH] <i>Reichsmarschall</i> Göring.
my name is Dr. Douglas Kelley.

203
00:12:26.704 --> 00:12:28.915
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

204
00:12:28.998 --> 00:12:30.917
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

205
00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:32.585
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH]
He says. "Wonderful. a doctor."

206
00:12:32.669 --> 00:12:34.420
I am. May I take your pulse?

207
00:12:34.504 --> 00:12:37.006
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

208
00:12:37.090 --> 00:12:38.716
<i>Ja. ja.</i> [CLEARS THROAT]

209
00:12:40.176 --> 00:12:42.178
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

210
00:12:42.261 --> 00:12:43.972
[IN ENGLISH] He's been asking
for his pills.

211
00:12:44.055 --> 00:12:45.890
- He wants you to get 'em for him.
- DOUGLAS: Mm-hmm.

212
00:12:45.974 --> 00:12:47.976
I understand you've had heart trouble.

213
00:12:48.059 --> 00:12:50.979
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

214
00:12:51.062 --> 00:12:53.189
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

215
00:12:53.648 --> 00:12:55.108
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "I've had
several minor heart attacks

216
00:12:55.191 --> 00:12:56.734
"and the pills help with that."

217
00:12:56.818 --> 00:12:58.361
Can you open your shirt. please?

218
00:12:58.444 --> 00:13:00.613
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

219
00:13:02.824 --> 00:13:04.200
- [SPEAKING GERMAN]
- DOUGLAS: Mm-hmm.

220
00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:09.163
[IN ENGLISH] Respiration is rapid
and shallow. Don't translate that.

221
00:13:10.999 --> 00:13:13.668
The pills help with the pain as well?

222
00:13:13.793 --> 00:13:15.628
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

223
00:13:15.712 --> 00:13:16.879
<i>Ja. ja.</i>

224
00:13:16.963 --> 00:13:19.549
[HERMANN SPEAKING GERMAN]

225
00:13:21.384 --> 00:13:23.428
[IN ENGLISH] He says he was
shot down in World War I.

226
00:13:23.511 --> 00:13:24.804
He has a bullet in his right hip.

227
00:13:24.887 --> 00:13:28.266
In 1923. he was shot in the groin

228
00:13:28.349 --> 00:13:29.434
during the Munich Putsch.

229
00:13:29.517 --> 00:13:30.727
You've been shot a lot. sir.

230
00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:32.520
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

231
00:13:32.645 --> 00:13:35.398
[LAUGHING. SPEAKING GERMAN]

232
00:13:35.481 --> 00:13:37.400
- [IN ENGLISH] "Occupational hazard."
- [DOUGLAS LAUGHS]

233
00:13:37.817 --> 00:13:40.319
Well. if you really
wanna look after your heart.

234
00:13:40.403 --> 00:13:42.697
the best way to do that
is to lose some weight.

235
00:13:42.864 --> 00:13:47.201
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

236
00:13:47.326 --> 00:13:49.579
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

237
00:13:49.662 --> 00:13:50.705
[PATS BELLY]

238
00:13:52.874 --> 00:13:54.250
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH]
"I assure you. you are looking

239
00:13:54.333 --> 00:13:56.127
"at the best physique in all of Germany.

240
00:13:56.210 --> 00:13:57.503
- "just ask my wife."
- [DOUGLAS CHUCKLES]

241
00:13:58.087 --> 00:14:01.174
I'm sure you're right. sir.
but the guards here call you "Fat Stuff."

242
00:14:05.803 --> 00:14:06.804
I'm sure...

243
00:14:07.597 --> 00:14:11.100
it would be difficult for a lesser man
to lose this weight.

244
00:14:11.184 --> 00:14:16.230
but you possess a fortitude and discipline
that others do not. yes?

245
00:14:18.357 --> 00:14:20.359
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

246
00:14:23.196 --> 00:14:24.530
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH]
"You see. this man is different."

247
00:14:25.323 --> 00:14:26.783
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

248
00:14:28.284 --> 00:14:30.495
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "We're gonna
be good friends. I'm sure of it."

249
00:14:31.954 --> 00:14:33.414
I look forward to that.

250
00:14:33.498 --> 00:14:34.916
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

251
00:14:34.999 --> 00:14:36.709
- [IN ENGLISH] Good day.
- HOWIE: <i>Auf Wiedersehen.</i>

252
00:14:37.585 --> 00:14:38.628
[DOOR OPENS]

253
00:14:41.339 --> 00:14:42.340
[DOOR CLOSES]

254
00:14:42.423 --> 00:14:43.466
[SIGHS SHAKILY]

255
00:14:43.549 --> 00:14:45.176
Inflated sense of self.

256
00:14:46.385 --> 00:14:47.386
Charming.

257
00:14:48.471 --> 00:14:49.555
Speaks English.

258
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:52.558
What? What? What?

259
00:14:52.642 --> 00:14:55.061
Yeah. the way he looked at me
when I called him fat.

260
00:14:55.144 --> 00:14:57.146
Yeah. he understood me.
He's been playing you.

261
00:14:58.231 --> 00:14:59.565
[HOWIE SIGHS]

262
00:14:59.649 --> 00:15:01.776
No. No. why... why would he pretend?

263
00:15:01.859 --> 00:15:04.737
Translation gives him more time
to consider his answers.

264
00:15:04.821 --> 00:15:06.656
He thinks that gives him an advantage.

265
00:15:08.616 --> 00:15:10.201
Wait. hold on. [SIGHS]

266
00:15:10.785 --> 00:15:12.829
You're saying I spent
the last three months

267
00:15:12.912 --> 00:15:14.872
mumbling to myself
while he understood every word?

268
00:15:14.956 --> 00:15:15.957
Pretty much.

269
00:15:16.958 --> 00:15:17.959
Jiminy.

270
00:15:18.668 --> 00:15:20.545
Are you... Are you gonna tell him
that you know?

271
00:15:20.628 --> 00:15:23.339
No. no.
No. he's gonna tell me when he's ready.

272
00:15:24.215 --> 00:15:26.968
- When's that?
- When he determines I'm not a threat.

273
00:15:28.427 --> 00:15:30.346
I wanna meet the rest of 'em. Who's next?

274
00:15:30.471 --> 00:15:33.474
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]
- Uh... Dr. Robert Ley.

275
00:15:34.517 --> 00:15:36.519
- Chief of the German Labor Front.
- DOUGLAS: Mmm-hmm.

276
00:15:36.602 --> 00:15:38.271
One of Hitler's earliest followers.

277
00:15:39.063 --> 00:15:41.274
<i>He once wrote a book that was
so complimentary of the</i> Führer

278
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:44.026
<i>that Hitler had the entire run destroyed
'cause he was so embarrassed.</i>

279
00:15:44.110 --> 00:15:45.945
[SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

280
00:15:46.028 --> 00:15:49.240
REPORTER: <i>Ley. who spearheaded
the Nazi slave labor program</i>

281
00:15:49.323 --> 00:15:51.033
<i>was captured in his pajamas.</i>

282
00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:53.536
<i>calling himself "Dr. Distelmeyer."</i>

283
00:15:54.579 --> 00:15:56.080
[LEY SPEAKING GERMAN]

284
00:15:58.666 --> 00:16:00.918
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "I'm not
like these other power-hungry men

285
00:16:01.002 --> 00:16:02.211
"you have locked up in here."

286
00:16:04.297 --> 00:16:05.381
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

287
00:16:06.757 --> 00:16:08.259
[IN ENGLISH] "I can smell the Jew."

288
00:16:11.012 --> 00:16:12.847
HOWIE: <i>Great Admiral Karl Dönitz.</i>

289
00:16:12.930 --> 00:16:15.141
<i>The German Navy's Commander-in-Chief.</i>

290
00:16:15.224 --> 00:16:17.894
<i>Architect of the U-boat attacks
that crippled the British Navy.</i>

291
00:16:17.977 --> 00:16:19.270
[SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

292
00:16:19.353 --> 00:16:22.565
REPORTER 2: [IN ENGLISH] <i>Dönitz condoned
murder of prisoners on the high seas.</i>

293
00:16:22.648 --> 00:16:23.900
[EXPLOSION]

294
00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:26.694
REPORTER 3: <i>A fanatical Nazi.
with the arrest of Dönitz.</i>

295
00:16:26.777 --> 00:16:28.988
<i>the Third Reich is ended forever.</i>

296
00:16:29.238 --> 00:16:31.282
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

297
00:16:32.366 --> 00:16:34.785
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "I have been
in custody for 76 days.

298
00:16:34.869 --> 00:16:38.372
"I have yet to be formally arrested
or charged with a specific crime.

299
00:16:38.456 --> 00:16:41.792
"which is a direct violation
of the Geneva Conventions.

300
00:16:41.876 --> 00:16:43.628
"Charge me or release me."

301
00:16:44.837 --> 00:16:48.090
HOWIE: <i>Julius Stretcher.
Hitler's Director of Propaganda.</i>

302
00:16:48.174 --> 00:16:50.009
<i>Publisher of the national
anti-Semitic paper.</i>

303
00:16:50.092 --> 00:16:51.135
Der Stürmer.

304
00:16:51.219 --> 00:16:52.220
REPORTER 4: <i>Stretcher!</i>

305
00:16:52.303 --> 00:16:56.474
<i>Dubbed the high priest of anti-Semitism
and the Beast of Franconia.</i>

306
00:16:56.557 --> 00:16:59.936
- <i>led the Jewish boycott...</i>
- [CROWD PROTESTING]

307
00:17:00.019 --> 00:17:03.231
REPORTER 4: <i>...and ruled Nuremberg
with an iron fist.</i>

308
00:17:03.314 --> 00:17:04.565
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

309
00:17:05.775 --> 00:17:07.151
[IN ENGLISH] He wants to know
if you're a Jew.

310
00:17:07.818 --> 00:17:09.028
DOUGLAS: No.

311
00:17:09.111 --> 00:17:11.739
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

312
00:17:12.531 --> 00:17:14.116
[IN ENGLISH] "But you work
in a Jewish profession."

313
00:17:16.244 --> 00:17:18.079
[TUTTING]

314
00:17:19.413 --> 00:17:21.791
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

315
00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:23.709
[IN ENGLISH]
"What do you fight for. Doctor?"

316
00:17:26.545 --> 00:17:29.257
- [ALL LAUGHING]
- DOUGLAS: <i>Göring is the key.</i>

317
00:17:29.340 --> 00:17:32.802
<i>The leader of a nation in exile.
He binds them all together.</i>

318
00:17:32.885 --> 00:17:33.928
[WHEEZING]

319
00:17:34.011 --> 00:17:37.890
DOUGLAS: <i>He's begun a strict self-imposed
diet and exercise regimen.</i>

320
00:17:37.974 --> 00:17:40.309
<i>and is going cold turkey on the pills.</i>

321
00:17:41.018 --> 00:17:43.646
<i>It's almost as if
he's training for something.</i>

322
00:17:44.522 --> 00:17:46.649
<i>If one were to write a book
about him. it...</i>

323
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:48.776
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

324
00:17:59.578 --> 00:18:01.205
Is there a library in town?

325
00:18:01.289 --> 00:18:03.332
- HOWIE: You wanna go to a library?
- Yes.

326
00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:06.127
- HOWIE: At 2:33 in the morning?
- Yes. Get your coat.

327
00:18:07.753 --> 00:18:08.754
[SIGHS]

328
00:18:08.838 --> 00:18:09.839
I'll get my coat.

329
00:18:12.008 --> 00:18:15.011
DOUGLAS: The sheer amount of narcissists
we got locked up in that hotel.

330
00:18:15.094 --> 00:18:17.263
I bet at least half have books in here

331
00:18:17.346 --> 00:18:20.016
written about them or written by them.

332
00:18:20.099 --> 00:18:22.059
We're gonna figure these guys out.

333
00:18:22.143 --> 00:18:24.645
HOWIE: Oh. yeah?
You speak a lot of German. Doc?

334
00:18:25.646 --> 00:18:27.398
DOUGLAS: Not even a little.
How'd you learn?

335
00:18:27.481 --> 00:18:31.444
My mother spoke German
and I wanted to be like her.

336
00:18:33.446 --> 00:18:34.905
You really think you can do it?

337
00:18:34.989 --> 00:18:36.073
DOUGLAS: Do what?

338
00:18:37.074 --> 00:18:40.036
Well. get these guys to open up to you.

339
00:18:40.119 --> 00:18:41.120
Sure.

340
00:18:42.830 --> 00:18:43.831
How?

341
00:18:45.750 --> 00:18:48.502
Everybody wants to be listened to.
It's a natural instinct.

342
00:18:49.837 --> 00:18:52.798
I learn about them.
I get them to trust me.

343
00:18:53.924 --> 00:18:54.925
They open up.

344
00:18:56.135 --> 00:18:57.511
Make it sound so easy. [CHUCKLES]

345
00:18:58.554 --> 00:19:00.389
What if we could dissect evil?

346
00:19:01.265 --> 00:19:03.934
I mean. what sets these men
apart from all the others?

347
00:19:04.018 --> 00:19:06.687
What enabled them
to commit the crimes that they did?

348
00:19:07.271 --> 00:19:08.814
They almost took over the world.

349
00:19:09.648 --> 00:19:11.609
You've heard
about the work camps for Jews?

350
00:19:15.488 --> 00:19:18.157
Rumor has it they weren't just work camps.

351
00:19:19.617 --> 00:19:20.618
I've heard.

352
00:19:21.369 --> 00:19:23.662
So. how do people become like that?

353
00:19:23.746 --> 00:19:26.248
We actually have a shot
to figure that out.

354
00:19:27.541 --> 00:19:32.046
To find out
what makes the Germans different.

355
00:19:32.922 --> 00:19:33.923
HOWIE: Different?

356
00:19:35.716 --> 00:19:36.717
DOUGLAS: From us.

357
00:19:38.636 --> 00:19:41.180
A man who writes a book about that
could make a lot of money.

358
00:19:46.143 --> 00:19:48.479
You know. for a second.
I thought you were being noble.

359
00:19:51.023 --> 00:19:52.066
You want noble?

360
00:19:54.026 --> 00:19:55.027
Fine.

361
00:19:55.111 --> 00:19:58.906
If we could psychologically define "evil."

362
00:20:00.408 --> 00:20:03.577
we could make sure something like this
never happens again.

363
00:20:08.999 --> 00:20:11.001
[ENGINE REVVING]

364
00:20:13.796 --> 00:20:16.090
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

365
00:20:17.508 --> 00:20:19.552
DOUGLAS: What's going on?
OFFICER: Hermann Göring can't breathe.

366
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:22.805
HOWIE: Move!
DOUGLAS: Howie!

367
00:20:24.765 --> 00:20:29.270
[HERMANN WHEEZING]

368
00:20:29.353 --> 00:20:30.354
DOUGLAS: <i>Herr.</i>

369
00:20:30.438 --> 00:20:32.189
- Okay. his airway is clear.
- HOWIE: That's good. right?

370
00:20:32.273 --> 00:20:33.357
DOUGLAS: No. he's having a heart attack.

371
00:20:33.441 --> 00:20:34.442
HOWIE: What?
DOUGLAS: Where the hell's

372
00:20:34.525 --> 00:20:35.693
- the prison doctor?
- CORPORAL: He's on his way.

373
00:20:35.776 --> 00:20:36.777
DOUGLAS: All right. Tell him to hurry.

374
00:20:36.861 --> 00:20:38.112
- Howie. I need some aspirin.
- Yeah.

375
00:20:38.195 --> 00:20:39.405
- DOUGLAS: Plain old ordinary aspirin.
- Got it! Got it!

376
00:20:39.488 --> 00:20:40.990
- Get it now! Go! Hey. hey. hey.
- [WHEEZING]

377
00:20:41.073 --> 00:20:43.784
Your heart's still beating.
which means you're alive.

378
00:20:43.868 --> 00:20:45.494
I'm gonna keep you that way. okay?

379
00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:47.329
I need you to stay calm. all right?

380
00:20:47.413 --> 00:20:51.125
Breathe with me. In and out. In and out.

381
00:20:51.834 --> 00:20:53.711
- [COUGHING]
- I'm here. I'm here. Look at me. I'm here.

382
00:20:53.794 --> 00:20:55.421
I'm not gonna let you die. all right?

383
00:20:56.130 --> 00:20:57.465
- In and...
- [GROANING]

384
00:20:57.548 --> 00:20:59.133
[HERMANN STRAINING]

385
00:20:59.550 --> 00:21:01.302
Here. Is that your wife?

386
00:21:01.969 --> 00:21:04.638
She's here. She's here. She's here.

387
00:21:04.722 --> 00:21:05.806
Breathe. Breathe with me.

388
00:21:05.890 --> 00:21:07.308
Doc's on his way.
Doc's on the way. Aspirin.

389
00:21:07.391 --> 00:21:09.935
DOUGLAS: Yeah. Hand me a few of those.
will ya? Thank you. Howie.

390
00:21:10.019 --> 00:21:12.354
Hey. hey. best thing for the heart.

391
00:21:12.438 --> 00:21:13.981
- plain old aspirin. Yeah.
- [HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

392
00:21:14.064 --> 00:21:15.065
[SPITS]

393
00:21:16.525 --> 00:21:17.568
Mmm... Mmm...

394
00:21:18.068 --> 00:21:20.571
- [IN ENGLISH] Trust me. all right?
- [HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

395
00:21:20.654 --> 00:21:22.406
DOUGLAS: [IN ENGLISH] Breathe.
In and out. Mm-hmm.

396
00:21:22.490 --> 00:21:25.075
- Chew. chew. Yeah. Better.
- [SPEAKING GERMAN]

397
00:21:25.159 --> 00:21:27.995
[IN ENGLISH]
Yeah. your pulse is slow. Yeah.

398
00:21:28.078 --> 00:21:31.957
Hey. guess what?
You're alive. You're alive.

399
00:21:32.625 --> 00:21:33.626
Well. how about that?

400
00:21:34.710 --> 00:21:35.711
Thank you.

401
00:21:35.794 --> 00:21:37.755
DOCTOR: Let's get him to the infirmary.
Come on.

402
00:21:49.433 --> 00:21:50.601
What're you smiling for?

403
00:21:51.018 --> 00:21:52.019
Hmm?

404
00:21:52.686 --> 00:21:53.729
[CHUCKLES]

405
00:21:54.146 --> 00:21:55.689
He said "thank you" in English.

406
00:21:58.609 --> 00:22:00.986
[UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING]

407
00:22:01.070 --> 00:22:03.781
Truman wants to win re-election in '48.

408
00:22:03.864 --> 00:22:07.159
He's not gonna do that coddling the Nazis.

409
00:22:07.243 --> 00:22:08.369
True enough.

410
00:22:08.452 --> 00:22:12.873
Plus. a trial means giving them a chance
to tell their stories to the world.

411
00:22:12.957 --> 00:22:14.750
What are we afraid to hear them tell?

412
00:22:15.251 --> 00:22:17.753
[SCOFFS] We won the damn war. Bob.

413
00:22:17.836 --> 00:22:22.049
If you do this. it'll turn into
the biggest boondoggle of all time.

414
00:22:22.132 --> 00:22:24.885
- Cameras in the damn courtroom...
- And what if they're sympathetic?

415
00:22:24.969 --> 00:22:27.638
What if all this does
is provide them with a platform

416
00:22:27.721 --> 00:22:29.598
for anti-Semitism all over the world?

417
00:22:30.307 --> 00:22:32.059
You wanna be responsible for that?

418
00:22:34.228 --> 00:22:36.480
[SIGHS] You wanna know if I'm comfortable

419
00:22:36.564 --> 00:22:39.858
executing a few Nazis without a trial?

420
00:22:39.942 --> 00:22:41.235
Damn right. I am.

421
00:22:43.654 --> 00:22:45.155
It doesn't matter anyway.

422
00:22:45.906 --> 00:22:47.199
You'll never get the Russians.

423
00:22:49.034 --> 00:22:50.828
ELSIE: We got the Russians.

424
00:22:50.911 --> 00:22:52.997
- What?
- ELSIE: We got the Russians.

425
00:22:53.789 --> 00:22:54.832
JACKSON: We did?

426
00:22:54.915 --> 00:22:56.750
Truman called Stalin himself.

427
00:22:56.834 --> 00:22:59.003
Looking at Nikitchenko
for lead prosecutor.

428
00:22:59.086 --> 00:23:00.421
That's fantastic news.

429
00:23:00.504 --> 00:23:01.964
I have no idea who you are.

430
00:23:02.756 --> 00:23:05.217
Colonel John Amen. sir.
I work for the Judge Advocate General.

431
00:23:06.552 --> 00:23:09.346
So. the Army sent us a lawyer? [CHUCKLES]

432
00:23:10.097 --> 00:23:11.098
Yes. sir.

433
00:23:11.181 --> 00:23:14.184
I bring greetings from General Eisenhower.
who says he wants you to know

434
00:23:14.268 --> 00:23:16.312
that he's not for hanging anyone
without a trial.

435
00:23:16.395 --> 00:23:17.771
ELSIE: Well. that's progress.

436
00:23:17.855 --> 00:23:19.732
He also says he hopes
the trial won't take too long

437
00:23:19.815 --> 00:23:21.275
so we can get on with hanging them.

438
00:23:21.358 --> 00:23:23.652
Hmm. Have a seat.

439
00:23:25.529 --> 00:23:27.364
I've read a lot about you. sir.

440
00:23:27.448 --> 00:23:29.033
They say you're gonna be
the next Chief Justice.

441
00:23:29.116 --> 00:23:31.243
President promised him
the seat personally.

442
00:23:31.327 --> 00:23:32.911
And swore me to secrecy.

443
00:23:32.995 --> 00:23:36.790
so let's maybe not tell everyone
who walks into the office about it. okay?

444
00:23:36.874 --> 00:23:39.877
Well. everyone in my office says
there's no way you get the trial.

445
00:23:40.753 --> 00:23:41.754
What do you say?

446
00:23:42.838 --> 00:23:44.173
I say I like an underdog.

447
00:23:45.424 --> 00:23:46.800
Good morning. Julius.

448
00:23:47.593 --> 00:23:50.971
I'm gonna show you a series of cards.
each with inkblots.

449
00:23:51.055 --> 00:23:54.058
and you're gonna tell me
what each inkblot makes you see.

450
00:23:54.141 --> 00:23:55.309
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

451
00:23:55.392 --> 00:23:58.520
DOUGLAS: [IN ENGLISH] Perhaps it will
reveal something about your character.

452
00:23:58.604 --> 00:24:01.398
your intelligence. creativity.

453
00:24:01.482 --> 00:24:03.692
And everything here stays between us.

454
00:24:08.572 --> 00:24:09.573
<i>Herr Doktor.</i>

455
00:24:11.033 --> 00:24:12.034
Yes.

456
00:24:13.243 --> 00:24:17.206
I can speak to you in English
if it is of some help.

457
00:24:19.375 --> 00:24:21.043
Only if it makes you comfortable.

458
00:24:22.127 --> 00:24:23.128
Shall we begin?

459
00:24:23.921 --> 00:24:25.798
- [SPEAKING GERMAN]
- HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "Butterfly."

460
00:24:25.881 --> 00:24:27.841
- [SPEAKING GERMAN]
- HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "Witch."

461
00:24:27.925 --> 00:24:29.968
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

462
00:24:30.052 --> 00:24:31.261
[IN ENGLISH] "Torpedo hit."

463
00:24:31.345 --> 00:24:33.138
Somebody has spilled something.

464
00:24:33.222 --> 00:24:34.682
[LAUGHS]

465
00:24:34.765 --> 00:24:36.725
I see 10.000 horses.

466
00:24:37.351 --> 00:24:40.646
I see the Valkyries ride.

467
00:24:42.648 --> 00:24:43.857
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

468
00:24:43.941 --> 00:24:44.942
[IN ENGLISH] "A vagina."

469
00:24:45.025 --> 00:24:46.068
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

470
00:24:46.151 --> 00:24:47.444
[IN ENGLISH] "A vagina."

471
00:24:48.153 --> 00:24:49.780
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

472
00:24:51.615 --> 00:24:53.075
[IN ENGLISH] "A Jewish vagina."

473
00:24:53.158 --> 00:24:54.368
DOUGLAS: Huh.

474
00:24:54.451 --> 00:24:55.661
This is blood.

475
00:24:55.744 --> 00:24:56.954
Whose blood?

476
00:24:59.832 --> 00:25:00.916
Or ink.

477
00:25:01.458 --> 00:25:03.377
You can say a lot of things with ink.

478
00:25:05.170 --> 00:25:07.506
GEORGE: [ON PHONE]
<i>I'm sorry. Bob. Word came down tonight.</i>

479
00:25:07.589 --> 00:25:08.799
<i>It's gonna be a no.</i>

480
00:25:08.882 --> 00:25:09.883
JACKSON: Mmm.

481
00:25:10.259 --> 00:25:11.385
[PHONE RECEIVER SLAMS]

482
00:25:11.468 --> 00:25:14.096
Congress is going to say no to the trial.

483
00:25:14.179 --> 00:25:15.973
They just want executions.

484
00:25:17.224 --> 00:25:18.851
- I'm out of moves.
- What about the President?

485
00:25:18.934 --> 00:25:22.062
President wants someone to hide behind.
that's why he needs Congress.

486
00:25:23.105 --> 00:25:24.982
Neither will do it without the other.

487
00:25:25.065 --> 00:25:27.860
- So you need someone bigger to back it.
- JOHN: Oh. come on.

488
00:25:27.943 --> 00:25:29.611
Who's bigger than the President?

489
00:25:32.823 --> 00:25:35.659
[CHURCH CHOIR VOCALIZING]

490
00:25:44.293 --> 00:25:46.044
Jesus Christ.

491
00:25:47.087 --> 00:25:48.088
Literally.

492
00:25:49.256 --> 00:25:51.300
- Are you a Catholic?
- I am now.

493
00:25:51.842 --> 00:25:54.261
[CARDINAL PANTING]

494
00:25:54.344 --> 00:25:56.013
The Holy Father will see you now.

495
00:25:56.096 --> 00:25:57.097
JACKSON: Hmm.

496
00:25:58.599 --> 00:26:02.269
POPE: You wish to put these men
on trial for their lives.

497
00:26:02.352 --> 00:26:05.606
and you have come to ask
for the Church's blessing in this.

498
00:26:06.732 --> 00:26:10.819
JACKSON: Your support would go a long way
to building an international consensus.

499
00:26:10.903 --> 00:26:12.905
POPE: No one denies these men are evil.

500
00:26:14.198 --> 00:26:15.657
But an eye for an eye...

501
00:26:17.201 --> 00:26:18.285
is not the answer.

502
00:26:18.368 --> 00:26:21.455
Maybe not. but I'm pretty sure
where I first read about it.

503
00:26:24.958 --> 00:26:26.084
Are you Catholic?

504
00:26:26.752 --> 00:26:27.753
No. sir.

505
00:26:29.129 --> 00:26:30.339
A religious man?

506
00:26:31.298 --> 00:26:32.341
Not especially.

507
00:26:32.424 --> 00:26:35.969
And yet. at home. they call you a Justice.

508
00:26:36.053 --> 00:26:37.387
I didn't pick the name.

509
00:26:37.471 --> 00:26:40.265
If you sit long enough
in judgement of others.

510
00:26:40.974 --> 00:26:45.854
you come to believe the laws of man
outweigh the laws of God.

511
00:26:48.106 --> 00:26:49.441
I don't believe that.

512
00:26:49.525 --> 00:26:50.692
Then...

513
00:26:52.778 --> 00:26:54.029
what do you believe?

514
00:26:56.907 --> 00:26:58.450
I believe in man.

515
00:26:58.534 --> 00:27:02.830
In our capacity to save ourselves
from men like the Nazis.

516
00:27:04.248 --> 00:27:06.124
I believe this to be a good act.

517
00:27:06.208 --> 00:27:09.628
One so good you must circumnavigate
your own laws to achieve it?

518
00:27:11.630 --> 00:27:16.134
I'm sorry. but the Catholic Church
cannot support you in this.

519
00:27:20.722 --> 00:27:23.183
But you could support them in 1933.

520
00:27:26.645 --> 00:27:27.938
I'm sorry?

521
00:27:28.772 --> 00:27:31.775
You signed the Concordat
with Hitler yourself.

522
00:27:33.527 --> 00:27:35.362
That was a different matter.

523
00:27:35.445 --> 00:27:38.991
You lived in Munich.
you were the nuncio to the German Empire.

524
00:27:39.074 --> 00:27:41.994
The Catholic Church
was the first world power

525
00:27:42.911 --> 00:27:44.913
to acknowledge the <i>Führer</i> State.

526
00:27:45.414 --> 00:27:47.165
You gave the Nazis credibility.

527
00:27:47.249 --> 00:27:49.668
In order to protect Catholics in Germany.

528
00:27:49.751 --> 00:27:54.548
Isn't it a pity the Jews
didn't have someone to do that for them?

529
00:27:56.008 --> 00:27:57.968
Do you think I condone what they did?

530
00:28:02.973 --> 00:28:04.808
People will remember. sir...

531
00:28:07.185 --> 00:28:09.563
what you did in 1933.

532
00:28:10.898 --> 00:28:12.441
what you do now.

533
00:28:13.483 --> 00:28:14.985
<i>They'll tell their children.</i>

534
00:28:17.571 --> 00:28:20.699
Did the Catholic Church
stand with the Nazis...

535
00:28:22.618 --> 00:28:23.911
or against them?

536
00:28:30.042 --> 00:28:31.668
Did you just blackmail the Pope?

537
00:28:31.752 --> 00:28:33.503
I don't wanna talk about it.

538
00:28:33.587 --> 00:28:35.672
[AIRCRAFT ENGINE WHIRRING]

539
00:28:36.757 --> 00:28:38.634
DOUGLAS: Word came down last night.

540
00:28:39.259 --> 00:28:40.552
There's gonna be a trial.

541
00:28:44.723 --> 00:28:45.766
A trial?

542
00:28:46.808 --> 00:28:47.851
[CHUCKLES]

543
00:28:47.935 --> 00:28:50.062
- Good. Good.
- [GROANS]

544
00:28:51.104 --> 00:28:52.564
As it should be. [CHUCKLES]

545
00:28:53.982 --> 00:28:56.610
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

546
00:29:01.865 --> 00:29:04.242
[IN ENGLISH]
Those cards that you showed me.

547
00:29:05.327 --> 00:29:07.287
what did they teach you about me?

548
00:29:08.789 --> 00:29:11.124
Honestly. that you are highly intelligent.

549
00:29:11.208 --> 00:29:12.376
Ah...

550
00:29:12.459 --> 00:29:14.252
I could have told you this.

551
00:29:14.336 --> 00:29:16.630
And that you're a narcissist

552
00:29:16.713 --> 00:29:20.634
given to an expansive
and aggressive fantasy life.

553
00:29:20.717 --> 00:29:24.388
with a strong ambition and drive
to subjugate the world

554
00:29:24.471 --> 00:29:26.974
as you find it
to your own pattern of thinking.

555
00:29:28.976 --> 00:29:30.644
And you were surprised by this?

556
00:29:32.104 --> 00:29:33.105
No.

557
00:29:33.855 --> 00:29:36.650
Then the cards have taught you nothing.

558
00:29:36.733 --> 00:29:37.943
[DOUGLAS CHUCKLES]

559
00:29:38.026 --> 00:29:40.988
HerrTriest. he tells me you do magic.

560
00:29:41.863 --> 00:29:42.990
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

561
00:29:44.825 --> 00:29:46.159
[IN ENGLISH] Sorry.

562
00:29:46.243 --> 00:29:47.244
Yes.

563
00:29:47.327 --> 00:29:50.288
Well. perhaps.
if it's not too much trouble.

564
00:29:50.372 --> 00:29:52.082
we don't get entertainment.

565
00:29:55.127 --> 00:29:56.128
Why not?

566
00:29:57.629 --> 00:30:01.508
Here's an average. ordinary silver dollar.

567
00:30:08.265 --> 00:30:09.599
Ta-da!

568
00:30:12.227 --> 00:30:13.395
- Very good.
- [CHUCKLES]

569
00:30:13.478 --> 00:30:14.521
HERMANN: Very good.

570
00:30:15.814 --> 00:30:18.483
I will show you a magic trick one day.

571
00:30:20.360 --> 00:30:21.486
What's that?

572
00:30:23.530 --> 00:30:26.033
I am going to escape the hangman's noose.

573
00:30:28.744 --> 00:30:30.871
And how do you plan on doing that?

574
00:30:32.998 --> 00:30:36.543
If I were to tell you.
it would not be a trick.

575
00:30:38.879 --> 00:30:39.880
LEY: Nuremberg.

576
00:30:43.091 --> 00:30:44.843
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

577
00:30:46.219 --> 00:30:47.888
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "Do you see
what the Allies are capable of?

578
00:30:47.971 --> 00:30:49.431
"There's nothing left."

579
00:30:51.683 --> 00:30:52.976
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

580
00:30:55.062 --> 00:30:56.063
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "Except that."

581
00:31:00.150 --> 00:31:01.777
[AIRCRAFT ENGINE RUMBLING]

582
00:31:05.655 --> 00:31:07.032
JACKSON: Palace of Justice.

583
00:31:08.825 --> 00:31:11.328
The roofs been damaged by the air raids.

584
00:31:12.579 --> 00:31:16.458
Fire gutted the upper floors
and collapsed the clock tower. but...

585
00:31:17.626 --> 00:31:21.463
this courtroom should be able to hold
600 people when it's finished.

586
00:31:22.464 --> 00:31:24.758
- ELSIE: What's with all the supplies?
- [JACKSON CHUCKLES]

587
00:31:24.841 --> 00:31:27.636
Nazis fought their last stand here
when the city was taken.

588
00:31:27.719 --> 00:31:29.221
MAN: And so they will again.

589
00:31:31.765 --> 00:31:34.226
Of all the beautiful cities
in this conquered land.

590
00:31:34.309 --> 00:31:37.229
you want to try them
in this bombed-out husk?

591
00:31:38.855 --> 00:31:42.400
This is Sir David Maxwell-Fyte.
assistant prosecutor for the British.

592
00:31:42.484 --> 00:31:43.693
[DAVID CHUCKLES]

593
00:31:43.777 --> 00:31:44.945
Yes. sir. we do.

594
00:31:45.028 --> 00:31:46.571
For one thing. we can control the space.

595
00:31:46.655 --> 00:31:49.533
For another. there's an adjoining prison
with room for up to 1.200 inmates.

596
00:31:50.117 --> 00:31:51.618
We only need space for 22.

597
00:31:52.410 --> 00:31:55.455
I'm sorry. Twenty-two. sir?

598
00:31:55.539 --> 00:31:59.042
That's the number of men
we're indicting for the first trial.

599
00:31:59.126 --> 00:32:04.005
You see. if we don't win that trial.
there won't be any more trials to come.

600
00:32:04.089 --> 00:32:06.633
And you. myself. and Justice Jackson.

601
00:32:06.716 --> 00:32:10.095
and our respective governments
will be the laughingstock of the world.

602
00:32:10.178 --> 00:32:13.265
defeated by the very men we've imprisoned.

603
00:32:13.348 --> 00:32:15.058
So. that will be fun.

604
00:32:17.018 --> 00:32:20.230
My friends in Washington
say opinion's turned against you.

605
00:32:20.313 --> 00:32:21.314
JACKSON: Oh. dear.

606
00:32:21.398 --> 00:32:25.193
DAVID: There's talk that you won't get
the Chief Justice's seat

607
00:32:25.277 --> 00:32:26.528
when Stone steps down.

608
00:32:26.611 --> 00:32:29.990
JACKSON: Who's Truman gonna pick?
Vinson? Vinson's too political.

609
00:32:30.073 --> 00:32:31.658
Yes. but he's there.

610
00:32:31.741 --> 00:32:33.451
This whole thing's
become a sideshow. Robert.

611
00:32:33.535 --> 00:32:34.619
It hasn't even begun.

612
00:32:35.787 --> 00:32:36.997
They say...

613
00:32:38.415 --> 00:32:40.709
you're writing all the briefs yourself.

614
00:32:40.792 --> 00:32:42.294
refusing help from other lawyers.

615
00:32:42.377 --> 00:32:43.795
Because it has to be done right.

616
00:32:43.879 --> 00:32:45.922
And it will. But you can't do it alone.

617
00:32:46.006 --> 00:32:49.259
Oh. everything will be fine
once we actually get to trial.

618
00:32:49.342 --> 00:32:52.429
[CHUCKLES] You say that as though
trying the Nazi High Command

619
00:32:52.512 --> 00:32:55.015
with untested case law
with the whole world watching

620
00:32:55.098 --> 00:32:56.099
is going to be the easy part.

621
00:32:58.101 --> 00:32:59.895
Well. when you put it like that...

622
00:32:59.978 --> 00:33:04.191
Anything less than total victory
will be considered utter defeat.

623
00:33:04.274 --> 00:33:06.568
Which means.
you don't just have to win. Robert.

624
00:33:06.651 --> 00:33:08.236
you have to be flawless.

625
00:33:09.738 --> 00:33:10.739
No pressure.

626
00:33:13.491 --> 00:33:14.868
I'll have another.

627
00:33:14.951 --> 00:33:16.453
ANDRUS: Your cells are made of stone.

628
00:33:16.536 --> 00:33:17.621
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

629
00:33:17.704 --> 00:33:19.206
ANDRUS: [IN ENGLISH] 9 feet by 13.

630
00:33:20.498 --> 00:33:22.459
Your beds are bolted to the wall.

631
00:33:23.251 --> 00:33:26.546
Your mattresses stuffed with straw
instead of springs.

632
00:33:27.631 --> 00:33:31.760
Your desks are made of cardboard
and will not support a man's full weight.

633
00:33:31.843 --> 00:33:34.846
Your chairs are never allowed
against any wall.

634
00:33:34.930 --> 00:33:38.558
and will be removed
every night at sundown.

635
00:33:39.392 --> 00:33:40.977
When you sleep.

636
00:33:41.061 --> 00:33:44.689
your head and hands will remain
above your blanket. visible at all times.

637
00:33:45.774 --> 00:33:49.236
You will be given no belts.
you'll be given no shoelaces.

638
00:33:49.319 --> 00:33:53.281
you'll be given no toilet seats.
you will be given nothing

639
00:33:53.365 --> 00:33:56.993
with which to use as a weapon
to take your own lives.

640
00:34:00.038 --> 00:34:01.289
Welcome to Nuremberg.

641
00:34:02.249 --> 00:34:04.209
[CELL DOORS CLANKING]

642
00:34:17.722 --> 00:34:18.807
[CELL DOOR CREAKS]

643
00:34:18.890 --> 00:34:20.558
- [CELL DOOR SLAMS]
- [LOCK CLICKS]

644
00:34:25.897 --> 00:34:27.857
[CRYING SOFTLY]

645
00:34:32.570 --> 00:34:33.571
Now this...

646
00:34:34.739 --> 00:34:35.865
is a cell.

647
00:34:36.408 --> 00:34:37.409
You approve?

648
00:34:37.492 --> 00:34:38.660
German-built.

649
00:34:40.036 --> 00:34:41.246
How could I not?

650
00:34:42.914 --> 00:34:44.249
[GROANS]

651
00:34:46.126 --> 00:34:47.877
They will charge us soon. yeah?

652
00:34:47.961 --> 00:34:49.713
You're looking forward to it?

653
00:34:49.796 --> 00:34:51.589
I believe I am.

654
00:34:52.924 --> 00:34:58.555
I will have. as you say.
"my day in court." [CHUCKLES]

655
00:35:00.765 --> 00:35:02.642
Do you know this Jackson?

656
00:35:02.726 --> 00:35:05.020
The Justice Jackson?

657
00:35:05.103 --> 00:35:06.187
No. I do not.

658
00:35:07.063 --> 00:35:08.857
He will try to outwit me...

659
00:35:10.567 --> 00:35:12.068
but he will not succeed.

660
00:35:12.777 --> 00:35:14.612
You're very sure of yourself.

661
00:35:14.696 --> 00:35:15.697
HERMANN: Doctor.

662
00:35:16.364 --> 00:35:19.659
no man has ever beaten me.

663
00:35:21.161 --> 00:35:25.290
There are books filled with the names
of those who have tried.

664
00:35:26.833 --> 00:35:28.126
Yet here you sit.

665
00:35:30.962 --> 00:35:31.963
German-built.

666
00:35:32.047 --> 00:35:33.965
[CHUCKLES]

667
00:35:34.883 --> 00:35:38.345
You think I am at some sort
of disadvantage

668
00:35:38.428 --> 00:35:39.846
because I sit in a cell?

669
00:35:41.681 --> 00:35:42.932
I will remind you.

670
00:35:44.059 --> 00:35:45.393
I surrendered.

671
00:35:46.519 --> 00:35:50.231
This is exactly where I desire to be.

672
00:35:51.274 --> 00:35:52.901
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

673
00:35:52.984 --> 00:35:55.487
DOUGLAS: <i>Göring remains an enigma to me.</i>

674
00:35:55.570 --> 00:35:59.741
<i>The closer we get to the indictments.
the more confident he becomes.</i>

675
00:35:59.824 --> 00:36:02.243
<i>I need to figure out a way
to get closer to him.</i>

676
00:36:02.911 --> 00:36:04.037
So. how do we do that?

677
00:36:04.454 --> 00:36:06.539
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

678
00:36:07.624 --> 00:36:09.167
We ask for his help.

679
00:36:10.210 --> 00:36:11.920
With what?

680
00:36:13.505 --> 00:36:14.547
Rudolf Hess.

681
00:36:15.215 --> 00:36:16.424
Rudolf...

682
00:36:16.508 --> 00:36:19.511
Rudolf Hess is coming here?

683
00:36:19.594 --> 00:36:21.429
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

684
00:36:23.598 --> 00:36:26.810
DOUGLAS: <i>Rudolf Hess.
Deputy to the</i> Führer.

685
00:36:26.893 --> 00:36:29.646
<i>Third in line for succession.
following Hitler and Göring.</i>

686
00:36:29.729 --> 00:36:31.272
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

687
00:36:31.356 --> 00:36:34.943
<i>Hess transcribed</i> Mein Kampf <i>for Hitler
while the two were in prison.</i>

688
00:36:35.026 --> 00:36:38.446
<i>and was known as one of his most
fanatical followers.</i>

689
00:36:38.530 --> 00:36:39.823
<i>Sieg Heil!</i>

690
00:36:40.657 --> 00:36:41.991
[RUDOLF GROANS]

691
00:36:42.075 --> 00:36:43.952
[IN ENGLISH] Never do that
in my prison again.

692
00:36:44.035 --> 00:36:45.787
[RUDOLF BREATHING HEAVILY]

693
00:36:51.251 --> 00:36:54.295
DOUGLAS: <i>On May 10. 1941.
at the height of the war.</i>

694
00:36:54.379 --> 00:36:58.299
<i>Hess climbed into
a Messerschmitt fighter plane alone</i>

695
00:36:58.383 --> 00:37:00.135
<i>and flew it over the North Sea.</i>

696
00:37:02.262 --> 00:37:04.139
[EXPLOSION]

697
00:37:05.682 --> 00:37:09.102
<i>He bailed out somewhere over Scotland
and broke his ankle upon impact.</i>

698
00:37:09.894 --> 00:37:13.231
<i>Upon his discovery.
he announced that he was Rudolf Hess.</i>

699
00:37:13.314 --> 00:37:15.358
<i>third in line of the German High Command.</i>

700
00:37:15.442 --> 00:37:17.402
<i>and he was here on a mission of peace.</i>

701
00:37:17.485 --> 00:37:20.071
<i>and wanted to speak
with Douglas Douglas-Hamilton.</i>

702
00:37:20.155 --> 00:37:22.115
<i>the 13th Duke of Hamilton</i>

703
00:37:22.198 --> 00:37:26.244
<i>whom Hess had met
at the 1936 Olympic Games in Berlin.</i>

704
00:37:27.078 --> 00:37:30.039
<i>After some obstacles.
Hess was granted his meeting.</i>

705
00:37:31.040 --> 00:37:34.836
<i>There. he announced his intention
to meet with King George VI.</i>

706
00:37:34.919 --> 00:37:36.713
<i>have Winston Churchill fired.</i>

707
00:37:36.796 --> 00:37:39.549
<i>and negotiate a truce with Britain.</i>

708
00:37:39.632 --> 00:37:42.177
<i>allowing the two nations to join forces</i>

709
00:37:42.260 --> 00:37:44.304
<i>and defeat the Soviet Union.</i>

710
00:37:45.597 --> 00:37:48.266
<i>Hess was immediately thrown
into the Tower of London.</i>

711
00:37:48.349 --> 00:37:50.226
<i>There. Hess began claiming</i>

712
00:37:50.310 --> 00:37:53.354
<i>he had no memory of past events.
even his childhood.</i>

713
00:37:54.022 --> 00:37:57.358
<i>This lasted until February. 1945.</i>

714
00:37:57.442 --> 00:38:00.904
<i>when he said his previous amnesia
had been faked.</i>

715
00:38:00.987 --> 00:38:02.071
<i>He then flipped again</i>

716
00:38:02.155 --> 00:38:05.992
<i>and said his amnesia
had returned in July. 1945.</i>

717
00:38:06.075 --> 00:38:07.619
<i>when Germany collapsed.</i>

718
00:38:07.702 --> 00:38:10.205
HERMANN: <i>So. now you have come
to Hermann Göring...</i>

719
00:38:11.122 --> 00:38:13.458
to discredit my old friend.

720
00:38:15.835 --> 00:38:19.422
What would be in this for me?

721
00:38:22.926 --> 00:38:23.927
What do you want?

722
00:38:27.680 --> 00:38:28.681
My wife...

723
00:38:29.641 --> 00:38:30.642
and my daughter.

724
00:38:32.519 --> 00:38:35.230
No one has been able to locate them
since I surrendered.

725
00:38:36.731 --> 00:38:38.566
I need you to find them for me. Doctor.

726
00:38:39.234 --> 00:38:41.819
To give to them these.

727
00:38:43.321 --> 00:38:44.322
Letters.

728
00:38:49.953 --> 00:38:51.454
First. we talk to Hess...

729
00:38:53.373 --> 00:38:54.624
and then your family.

730
00:38:57.001 --> 00:38:58.002
DOUGLAS: How about that?

731
00:38:58.086 --> 00:39:00.547
So. what. this guy almost
takes over the whole world

732
00:39:00.630 --> 00:39:03.216
and now you want us to do
a mail run for him? Doc!

733
00:39:03.299 --> 00:39:05.802
I'm in deeper with this guy
than anyone's ever been.

734
00:39:05.885 --> 00:39:08.805
and meeting his family
will only tell me more.

735
00:39:10.515 --> 00:39:12.100
HERMANN: <i>So. Rudolf...</i>

736
00:39:14.102 --> 00:39:15.728
do you remember me?

737
00:39:19.774 --> 00:39:21.150
We were together. yes.

738
00:39:22.610 --> 00:39:24.070
That must have been the case.

739
00:39:25.363 --> 00:39:27.073
But I don't remember anyone.

740
00:39:27.907 --> 00:39:28.950
[CHUCKLES]

741
00:39:29.909 --> 00:39:31.703
It was the three of us. Rudolf.

742
00:39:33.329 --> 00:39:34.330
You...

743
00:39:35.039 --> 00:39:36.040
and I...

744
00:39:38.501 --> 00:39:39.544
and Adolf.

745
00:39:41.337 --> 00:39:42.714
We ruled an empire.

746
00:39:46.092 --> 00:39:47.343
I'm sorry.

747
00:39:52.223 --> 00:39:53.891
You may well have been a friend...

748
00:39:56.352 --> 00:39:58.062
but I don't know you anymore.

749
00:40:04.110 --> 00:40:05.278
HERMANN: <i>He's lying.</i>

750
00:40:06.821 --> 00:40:10.241
He has just spent an hour to say
he does not remember me.

751
00:40:12.201 --> 00:40:15.079
But when he arrived in the prison
and he saw me...

752
00:40:16.581 --> 00:40:17.665
what did he do?

753
00:40:18.875 --> 00:40:19.876
Salute.

754
00:40:21.294 --> 00:40:22.295
<i>Sieg Heil.</i>

755
00:40:25.673 --> 00:40:27.008
[IN ENGLISH] That was very good.

756
00:40:33.014 --> 00:40:34.098
This is dumb.

757
00:40:34.724 --> 00:40:35.725
I'm dumb.

758
00:40:35.808 --> 00:40:37.685
- I knew you'd come through for me.
- HOWIE: Yeah.

759
00:40:37.769 --> 00:40:39.520
'Cause I'm a dummy.

760
00:40:39.604 --> 00:40:40.813
[DOUGLAS LAUGHING]

761
00:40:44.817 --> 00:40:45.860
DOUGLAS: How'd you find 'em?

762
00:40:45.943 --> 00:40:48.071
HOWIE: Local gossip told me
they're in Veldenstein.

763
00:40:48.905 --> 00:40:49.906
Smoke?

764
00:40:54.869 --> 00:40:56.037
Never see you smoke.

765
00:40:57.080 --> 00:40:58.623
Yeah. I don't. Gave it up.

766
00:40:59.916 --> 00:41:01.125
My parents hated it.

767
00:41:03.252 --> 00:41:04.671
You always got 'em on ya.

768
00:41:04.754 --> 00:41:06.756
It's a trick to get in good
with the officers.

769
00:41:08.383 --> 00:41:10.468
Tell myself I'll have a smoke
when the war is done.

770
00:41:11.052 --> 00:41:12.679
The war is done. Howie.

771
00:41:14.180 --> 00:41:15.515
It's not too much farther.

772
00:41:24.232 --> 00:41:26.943
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

773
00:41:28.111 --> 00:41:30.113
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

774
00:41:30.196 --> 00:41:31.406
[DOOR OPENS]

775
00:41:32.156 --> 00:41:34.200
[HOWIE SPEAKING GERMAN]

776
00:41:36.119 --> 00:41:37.161
EMMY: Franz?

777
00:41:37.912 --> 00:41:39.163
[SPEAKING GERMAN. GASPS]

778
00:41:39.247 --> 00:41:40.373
[HOWIE SPEAKING GERMAN]

779
00:41:40.456 --> 00:41:41.916
DOUGLAS: [IN ENGLISH] Mrs. Göring?

780
00:41:43.459 --> 00:41:45.128
- Mrs. Göring...
- [DOOR CLOSES]

781
00:41:46.337 --> 00:41:48.172
my name is Douglas Kelley.

782
00:41:49.048 --> 00:41:51.217
I work at the prison. I'm a psychiatrist.

783
00:41:52.719 --> 00:41:54.470
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

784
00:42:01.728 --> 00:42:04.772
[IN ENGLISH] Your husband asked me
to bring you some letters.

785
00:42:04.856 --> 00:42:06.357
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

786
00:42:08.985 --> 00:42:09.986
Hermann?

787
00:42:11.404 --> 00:42:12.405
[IN ENGLISH] Yes.

788
00:42:15.408 --> 00:42:17.410
[PIANO PLAYING FAINTLY]

789
00:42:25.501 --> 00:42:26.544
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

790
00:42:27.253 --> 00:42:28.671
- HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "How is he?"
- He's good.

791
00:42:29.756 --> 00:42:30.757
He's holdin' up.

792
00:42:31.674 --> 00:42:32.925
[DOUGLAS CHUCKLES]

793
00:42:34.510 --> 00:42:35.720
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

794
00:42:37.180 --> 00:42:38.347
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

795
00:42:41.684 --> 00:42:43.728
- [PIANO STOPS]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

796
00:42:44.479 --> 00:42:45.480
EMMY: Edda.

797
00:42:48.065 --> 00:42:49.150
[IN ENGLISH] Was that you playing?

798
00:42:52.361 --> 00:42:53.362
It was beautiful.

799
00:42:55.239 --> 00:42:56.866
[BOTH SPEAKING GERMAN]

800
00:43:05.750 --> 00:43:08.002
[IN ENGLISH] Uh. she said.
"He's a friend of your father."

801
00:43:10.171 --> 00:43:11.172
Edda...

802
00:43:13.424 --> 00:43:14.467
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

803
00:43:15.343 --> 00:43:16.385
[IN ENGLISH] "How is Papa?"

804
00:43:17.762 --> 00:43:19.180
Ah. he...

805
00:43:20.640 --> 00:43:22.099
[SMACKS LIPS] He's doing very well.

806
00:43:22.183 --> 00:43:23.351
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

807
00:43:23.434 --> 00:43:25.686
- HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "Is he being brave?"
- Very brave.

808
00:43:28.648 --> 00:43:30.358
He wants you to be brave. too.

809
00:43:31.484 --> 00:43:33.027
[TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

810
00:43:38.032 --> 00:43:39.325
DOUGLAS: [IN ENGLISH]
He wrote you a letter.

811
00:43:39.408 --> 00:43:41.202
[HOWIE TRANSLATING IN GERMAN]

812
00:43:42.703 --> 00:43:43.913
[EDDA CHUCKLES]

813
00:43:48.042 --> 00:43:49.043
<i>Danke.</i>

814
00:43:50.586 --> 00:43:52.713
[EMMY SPEAKING GERMAN]

815
00:43:52.797 --> 00:43:54.924
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH]
"She will read it 100 times. Thank you."

816
00:43:55.007 --> 00:43:56.008
EMMY: <i>Danke.</i>

817
00:44:01.222 --> 00:44:02.390
[DOOR OPENS]

818
00:44:03.975 --> 00:44:04.976
EMMY: <i>Doktor!</i>

819
00:44:10.898 --> 00:44:11.899
[IN ENGLISH] For Hermann.

820
00:44:13.484 --> 00:44:14.652
I don't know if I can.

821
00:44:14.735 --> 00:44:15.736
<i>Bitte.</i>

822
00:44:26.706 --> 00:44:27.790
[IN ENGLISH] Okay.

823
00:44:29.375 --> 00:44:30.585
Come back.

824
00:44:40.428 --> 00:44:41.429
You okay. Doc?

825
00:44:42.513 --> 00:44:44.891
[ENGINE STARTS]

826
00:44:44.974 --> 00:44:47.643
[ENGINE ACCELERATING]

827
00:44:53.608 --> 00:44:55.693
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [CAMERAS FLASHING]

828
00:44:56.861 --> 00:44:57.862
What the hell?

829
00:44:57.945 --> 00:45:01.824
- [CAMERAS FLASHING]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

830
00:45:03.576 --> 00:45:06.037
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

831
00:45:06.120 --> 00:45:07.330
DOUGLAS: What's goin' on?

832
00:45:07.413 --> 00:45:10.166
Word came down a couple of hours ago.
We're charging the prisoners.

833
00:45:11.083 --> 00:45:12.084
Where have you been?

834
00:45:15.630 --> 00:45:16.797
[SIGHS]

835
00:45:18.257 --> 00:45:22.053
[LOCKS CLICKING. DOOR CREAKING]

836
00:45:27.266 --> 00:45:28.267
Hermann Göring?

837
00:45:29.477 --> 00:45:32.480
I am <i>Reichsmarschall</i> Hermann Göring.

838
00:45:33.147 --> 00:45:35.441
[INHALES] Hermann Wilhelm Göring.
you are hereby charged

839
00:45:35.524 --> 00:45:37.818
by the United States of America.
the French Republic.

840
00:45:37.902 --> 00:45:39.946
United Kingdom of Great Britain
and Northern Ireland

841
00:45:40.029 --> 00:45:43.449
and the Union of Soviet Socialist
Republics on the following four counts.

842
00:45:43.532 --> 00:45:46.702
Crimes against Peace. War Crimes.
Crimes against Humanity

843
00:45:46.786 --> 00:45:49.622
and of a Common Plan or Conspiracy
to commit those Crimes.

844
00:45:49.705 --> 00:45:52.291
The Crimes against Humanity
you're accused of include murder.

845
00:45:52.375 --> 00:45:55.544
extermination. enslavement.
deportation. and other inhumane acts.

846
00:45:55.628 --> 00:45:57.672
This is a copy of your indictment.
Do you have any questions?

847
00:45:57.755 --> 00:45:59.674
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

848
00:45:59.757 --> 00:46:00.758
<i>Nein.</i>

849
00:46:01.968 --> 00:46:02.969
Good day.

850
00:46:04.929 --> 00:46:06.097
Who's next?

851
00:46:06.180 --> 00:46:07.181
Stretcher.

852
00:46:13.270 --> 00:46:15.189
[DOOR CREAKING. SLAMS]

853
00:46:18.109 --> 00:46:19.819
Do you have any questions?

854
00:46:19.902 --> 00:46:20.903
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

855
00:46:21.529 --> 00:46:24.198
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

856
00:46:24.281 --> 00:46:25.491
[IN ENGLISH] What did he say?

857
00:46:26.951 --> 00:46:29.036
He said he wants a Jewish lawyer.

858
00:46:29.704 --> 00:46:31.122
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

859
00:46:31.205 --> 00:46:32.498
[IN ENGLISH] "I'm not going to trial."

860
00:46:33.499 --> 00:46:34.750
You are. Dr. Ley.

861
00:46:35.668 --> 00:46:37.378
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

862
00:46:38.212 --> 00:46:39.505
[IN ENGLISH] "I never killed anyone."

863
00:46:39.922 --> 00:46:41.924
[SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

864
00:46:42.008 --> 00:46:43.342
[IN ENGLISH] Guards!

865
00:46:43.426 --> 00:46:44.677
It's okay. it's okay.

866
00:46:44.760 --> 00:46:45.761
- LEY: Don't touch me.
- It's okay.

867
00:46:45.845 --> 00:46:46.929
- Robert. Robert...
- LEY: Don't touch me!

868
00:46:47.013 --> 00:46:48.389
- HOWIE: Whoa. whoa!
- Hold him!

869
00:46:48.472 --> 00:46:49.390
LEY: Come on!

870
00:46:49.473 --> 00:46:50.474
ANDRUS: Get a hold of him!

871
00:46:50.558 --> 00:46:53.728
LEY: Don't try me as a common criminal!
Come on!

872
00:46:53.811 --> 00:46:56.022
Shoot me! Shoot me!

873
00:46:56.105 --> 00:46:57.648
Shoot me!

874
00:46:57.732 --> 00:46:59.734
[SINGING UPBEAT JAZZ SONG]

875
00:47:25.885 --> 00:47:26.886
Rough day?

876
00:47:27.803 --> 00:47:29.388
Lady from the train.

877
00:47:29.972 --> 00:47:31.057
Magic man.

878
00:47:32.224 --> 00:47:33.559
How goes the secret mission?

879
00:47:35.770 --> 00:47:37.438
It's hit a few obstacles.

880
00:47:38.564 --> 00:47:39.732
[BLOWS]

881
00:47:40.483 --> 00:47:41.609
I can see that.

882
00:47:42.818 --> 00:47:44.236
What are you doing here?

883
00:47:45.738 --> 00:47:47.156
I came in with the press.

884
00:47:47.907 --> 00:47:50.159
Hermann Göring and the Nazis
are being indicted today.

885
00:47:50.242 --> 00:47:51.368
You don't say?

886
00:47:52.495 --> 00:47:54.580
[INHALES] Strap yourself in.

887
00:47:55.706 --> 00:47:58.334
This city is about to become
"The Greatest Show on Earth."

888
00:47:59.710 --> 00:48:02.713
[JAZZ MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

889
00:48:12.264 --> 00:48:16.769
[LOCKS CLICKING. DOOR CREAKING]

890
00:48:22.399 --> 00:48:24.026
[EXHALES]

891
00:48:28.072 --> 00:48:29.073
From your wife.

892
00:48:33.119 --> 00:48:34.120
HERMANN: You saw her?

893
00:48:38.040 --> 00:48:39.125
<i>Danke schön.</i> Doctor.

894
00:48:45.214 --> 00:48:49.677
[LIVELY NEWS INTRO MUSIC PLAYING]

895
00:48:50.678 --> 00:48:54.473
REPORTER: <i>Dateline Nuremberg!
As dark rumors continue to swirl</i>

896
00:48:54.557 --> 00:48:57.059
<i>about the true purpose
of the Nazi work camps.</i>

897
00:48:57.143 --> 00:49:00.229
<i>the legal teams are assembling
for what promises to be</i>

898
00:49:00.312 --> 00:49:02.064
<i>the trial of the century.</i>

899
00:49:02.148 --> 00:49:05.609
<i>Through this tunnel.
the Nazis will be taken to the courtroom.</i>

900
00:49:05.693 --> 00:49:07.903
<i>now being rebuilt for the trial.</i>

901
00:49:07.987 --> 00:49:09.613
<i>There. the film lights will be so bright</i>

902
00:49:09.697 --> 00:49:12.950
<i>that the court-goers
will be provided with sunglasses.</i>

903
00:49:13.033 --> 00:49:15.119
<i>Hermann Göring
and his Hitler-loving cronies</i>

904
00:49:15.202 --> 00:49:17.705
<i>are scheduled to face off
with our boys in one week.</i>

905
00:49:17.788 --> 00:49:21.625
<i>Will justice prevail?
Or will the fascists go free?</i>

906
00:49:21.709 --> 00:49:26.046
<i>This reporter desperately hopes
that the Allies run into no problems.</i>

907
00:49:27.339 --> 00:49:28.340
JOHN: We have a problem.

908
00:49:28.424 --> 00:49:32.303
Operation Weserübung
was the German invasion of Denmark

909
00:49:32.386 --> 00:49:33.888
and Norway in 1940.

910
00:49:33.971 --> 00:49:35.514
Textbook aggressive war.

911
00:49:35.598 --> 00:49:38.100
The Nazis. they roll tanks in.
they occupy neutral country.

912
00:49:38.184 --> 00:49:42.688
Except they're going to claim
that the invasion was a preemptive strike.

913
00:49:42.771 --> 00:49:44.023
To preempt what?

914
00:49:44.773 --> 00:49:46.108
The British plan to invade Norway.

915
00:49:46.192 --> 00:49:48.360
- Well. that's ridiculous.
- DAVID: Absolutely ridiculous.

916
00:49:49.028 --> 00:49:50.487
I'm in complete agreement.

917
00:49:51.780 --> 00:49:54.408
It concerns me that you're in this room
right now.

918
00:49:54.491 --> 00:49:57.703
Well. in addition to being ridiculous.

919
00:49:57.786 --> 00:49:58.954
it also happens to be true.

920
00:49:59.038 --> 00:50:02.625
The idea was to use the country
as a staging area to hold the Nazis back.

921
00:50:02.708 --> 00:50:06.420
We can't prosecute the Nazis
for planning aggressive wars

922
00:50:06.503 --> 00:50:08.797
if you guys were planning aggressive wars.

923
00:50:08.881 --> 00:50:10.299
I admit there's a certain logic there.

924
00:50:10.382 --> 00:50:11.759
Can the Nazis prove it?

925
00:50:11.842 --> 00:50:13.886
The German lawyer's
already put in a request for documents.

926
00:50:13.969 --> 00:50:15.971
- but they don't have it. Not yet.
- Then we're in the clear.

927
00:50:16.055 --> 00:50:17.056
Maybe.

928
00:50:18.307 --> 00:50:20.434
But it raises a bigger issue.

929
00:50:21.393 --> 00:50:25.522
We have to know what the Nazis know.
what their defense strategy is.

930
00:50:26.190 --> 00:50:28.234
How exactly do you propose we do that?

931
00:50:29.443 --> 00:50:31.612
[ENGINE WHIRRING]

932
00:50:31.695 --> 00:50:36.158
ANDRUS: <i>Dr. Kelley. you are going to meet
someone very important this evening.</i>

933
00:50:37.284 --> 00:50:39.870
<i>This might actually be your chance
to finally be of some use.</i>

934
00:50:39.954 --> 00:50:42.957
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

935
00:50:45.709 --> 00:50:46.877
JACKSON: Impressive. right?

936
00:50:50.172 --> 00:50:53.217
Hitler was building it
to be the largest stadium on the planet.

937
00:50:55.552 --> 00:50:56.887
You're Justice Jackson.

938
00:50:58.055 --> 00:50:59.181
JACKSON: And you're the shrink.

939
00:51:01.016 --> 00:51:02.935
This is where they held the rallies.

940
00:51:03.018 --> 00:51:07.106
Every year. Hitler would pack this place.
speak to the Nazi Party as a whole.

941
00:51:08.274 --> 00:51:09.358
They filmed it.

942
00:51:11.735 --> 00:51:15.406
In 1935. this is where he announced
the Nuremberg Laws.

943
00:51:15.990 --> 00:51:17.074
You know the laws?

944
00:51:19.201 --> 00:51:21.203
The Nuremberg Laws defined a Jew

945
00:51:21.287 --> 00:51:24.498
as any person having
three or four Jewish grandparents.

946
00:51:25.874 --> 00:51:28.085
And it didn't matter
if you practiced Judaism.

947
00:51:28.168 --> 00:51:32.756
if you'd converted to Christianity.
this was about blood.

948
00:51:35.342 --> 00:51:38.721
The laws stripped all Jews
of German citizenry.

949
00:51:40.014 --> 00:51:43.851
They made it illegal for Jews and Germans
to marry each other

950
00:51:43.934 --> 00:51:46.145
because of the fear of <i>Rassenschande.</i>

951
00:51:46.979 --> 00:51:48.731
Defilement of the blood.

952
00:51:51.400 --> 00:51:55.863
Under the laws. Jews were prohibited
from using state hospitals.

953
00:51:56.613 --> 00:52:00.451
and not allowed access to public education
beyond the age of 14.

954
00:52:02.036 --> 00:52:05.289
Libraries. parks. and beaches
were closed to Jews.

955
00:52:06.749 --> 00:52:09.918
War memorials
had all Jewish names on them...

956
00:52:11.253 --> 00:52:12.254
expunged.

957
00:52:13.589 --> 00:52:18.302
All of that was announced right here.
on this very ground.

958
00:52:22.765 --> 00:52:24.016
What do you want from me?

959
00:52:25.809 --> 00:52:27.394
Your patients...

960
00:52:28.604 --> 00:52:31.523
I need you to start asking them
the right questions.

961
00:52:34.777 --> 00:52:36.528
What are the right questions?

962
00:52:37.738 --> 00:52:39.531
What they tell their lawyers.

963
00:52:39.615 --> 00:52:41.742
How they plan to defend themselves.

964
00:52:44.078 --> 00:52:46.246
[DOUGLAS SCOFFS]

965
00:52:46.330 --> 00:52:47.748
You want me to be a spy.

966
00:52:49.583 --> 00:52:51.377
I want you to do your duty
for your country.

967
00:52:51.460 --> 00:52:54.838
No. you want me to break
doctor-patient confidentiality.

968
00:52:54.922 --> 00:52:58.217
I think you already have. Doctor.
We read every report.

969
00:52:59.093 --> 00:53:00.094
We need more.

970
00:53:02.638 --> 00:53:03.972
[LIGHTER CLICKING]

971
00:53:11.855 --> 00:53:13.148
Why not just shoot them?

972
00:53:15.150 --> 00:53:16.568
That's what everybody wants.

973
00:53:17.361 --> 00:53:19.571
- I mean. if you're just gonna cheat...
- It's not cheating.

974
00:53:19.655 --> 00:53:21.782
If you're asking me to betray my oath...

975
00:53:24.576 --> 00:53:26.745
why not just shoot them
and be done with it?

976
00:53:30.332 --> 00:53:33.168
After the last Great War.
we made Germany crawl.

977
00:53:34.920 --> 00:53:36.463
We humiliated them.

978
00:53:36.547 --> 00:53:38.799
Made them pay reparations
they couldn't afford.

979
00:53:40.342 --> 00:53:44.012
We made them hate us so much that
in less than two decades.

980
00:53:45.097 --> 00:53:48.559
they went from a broken nation
to near world conquerors.

981
00:53:50.310 --> 00:53:52.438
We have to do this right.
because if we don't...

982
00:53:53.981 --> 00:53:57.151
if 15 years from now.
they come back even stronger...

983
00:53:58.986 --> 00:54:01.071
I don't know if we can beat 'em
a third time.

984
00:54:04.324 --> 00:54:06.827
If we just shoot these men.
we make 'em martyrs.

985
00:54:07.911 --> 00:54:09.371
I'm not gonna allow them that.

986
00:54:10.664 --> 00:54:12.458
There will be no statues of them.

987
00:54:13.834 --> 00:54:15.377
No songs of praise.

988
00:54:17.713 --> 00:54:20.007
I'm gonna put Hermann Göring
on the stand

989
00:54:21.383 --> 00:54:23.719
and I'm gonna make him tell the world
what he did.

990
00:54:25.762 --> 00:54:27.639
So that it can never happen again.

991
00:54:29.016 --> 00:54:30.476
[EXHALES]

992
00:54:31.685 --> 00:54:32.853
Hmm.

993
00:54:35.689 --> 00:54:37.274
You brought me here because of Göring?

994
00:54:38.400 --> 00:54:39.401
No.

995
00:54:42.779 --> 00:54:47.409
I brought you here to show you
that before the bullets were fired.

996
00:54:48.911 --> 00:54:51.413
before tens of millions of men died...

997
00:54:54.208 --> 00:54:56.126
all of this started with laws.

998
00:54:57.836 --> 00:55:01.089
This war ends in a courtroom.

999
00:55:03.425 --> 00:55:04.426
With Göring.

1000
00:55:05.427 --> 00:55:07.221
JACKSON: He's the face of the Nazis now.

1001
00:55:08.514 --> 00:55:10.432
As he falls. so do they all.

1002
00:55:12.726 --> 00:55:14.311
But if I'm gonna do that. I...

1003
00:55:16.647 --> 00:55:18.106
I need to be ready for him.

1004
00:55:22.653 --> 00:55:23.779
Will you help me?

1005
00:55:27.908 --> 00:55:30.452
- [RAIN PATTERING]
- [THUNDER RUMBLING]

1006
00:55:39.378 --> 00:55:40.546
[EXHALES]

1007
00:55:41.421 --> 00:55:42.506
Let's talk about Hitler.

1008
00:55:46.927 --> 00:55:50.514
It is interesting you have not
asked me this directly before.

1009
00:55:51.431 --> 00:55:54.184
I'm curious what the attraction was.

1010
00:55:55.811 --> 00:55:57.688
He was a failed painter. right?

1011
00:55:57.771 --> 00:56:01.942
Not a very good soldier.
yet he's worshiped and revered.

1012
00:56:04.653 --> 00:56:06.446
He made us feel German again.

1013
00:56:11.994 --> 00:56:12.995
How?

1014
00:56:15.038 --> 00:56:17.207
Well. the war had seen Germany crushed.

1015
00:56:18.333 --> 00:56:24.214
And along comes a man who says.
"We can reclaim our former glory."

1016
00:56:26.842 --> 00:56:28.510
Would you not follow a man like this?

1017
00:56:29.928 --> 00:56:31.888
Depends what else he wanted to do.

1018
00:56:35.267 --> 00:56:38.895
The first time I saw Hitler talk.
it was. uh...

1019
00:56:40.814 --> 00:56:41.857
1922.

1020
00:56:42.816 --> 00:56:46.111
Upstairs of a coffee shop.
For maybe 30 people.

1021
00:56:47.821 --> 00:56:48.905
This was peacetime.

1022
00:56:48.989 --> 00:56:52.701
but it was a peace without food.
jobs. shoes.

1023
00:56:54.161 --> 00:56:56.163
And he stood up. and he said.

1024
00:56:56.246 --> 00:57:00.500
"French bellies are being filled
with German pain."

1025
00:57:01.835 --> 00:57:02.836
Then.

1026
00:57:04.046 --> 00:57:07.132
"if you make threats.
you need bayonets.

1027
00:57:07.758 --> 00:57:10.344
"Rearm! Down with Versailles!"

1028
00:57:12.638 --> 00:57:16.516
So. that night.
I became a National Socialist.

1029
00:57:18.518 --> 00:57:21.605
Off of... one speech?

1030
00:57:21.688 --> 00:57:25.067
Well. I could tell he would appeal
to the old soldiers.

1031
00:57:25.150 --> 00:57:27.694
If we have the old soldiers.
we have the manpower.

1032
00:57:27.778 --> 00:57:31.823
Even with his anti-Semitism.
it served a practical purpose.

1033
00:57:32.532 --> 00:57:36.620
It brought towards us men who needed
something else to focus their emotions.

1034
00:57:36.703 --> 00:57:37.996
Something else to blame.

1035
00:57:40.999 --> 00:57:42.000
And the camps?

1036
00:57:47.339 --> 00:57:52.636
[SIGHS] They were to be work camps
for our political opponents. nothing more.

1037
00:57:53.553 --> 00:57:54.763
And you signed off on that?

1038
00:57:55.389 --> 00:57:56.556
HERMANN: For work camps. yeah.

1039
00:57:56.640 --> 00:57:58.475
Do you not think

1040
00:57:58.558 --> 00:58:02.062
that the Japanese interned by
the Americans after Pearl Harbor

1041
00:58:02.145 --> 00:58:04.064
were not put to work?
Of course. they were.

1042
00:58:06.441 --> 00:58:09.569
I made the camps for the good of Germany.
for the war effort.

1043
00:58:11.822 --> 00:58:12.948
Not for death.

1044
00:58:15.325 --> 00:58:17.327
Himmler. Heydrich.

1045
00:58:18.412 --> 00:58:19.621
They were responsible?

1046
00:58:22.082 --> 00:58:26.128
If it is true what they say happened
in the camps...

1047
00:58:28.213 --> 00:58:31.258
this is a grave blight
on the great German Reich.

1048
00:58:34.970 --> 00:58:36.888
Have you told your lawyer about this?

1049
00:58:39.474 --> 00:58:43.103
Douglas. I will not stand
against the <i>Führer.</i>

1050
00:58:45.105 --> 00:58:47.107
Not even if it could help you?

1051
00:58:47.190 --> 00:58:50.193
These are not things people
need to know. Doctor.

1052
00:58:52.571 --> 00:58:53.572
Only you.

1053
00:58:56.199 --> 00:58:57.743
He can be sympathetic.

1054
00:58:59.327 --> 00:59:00.954
It's gonna be a problem for you.

1055
00:59:01.037 --> 00:59:03.790
He seriously claims that he thought
they were only work camps?

1056
00:59:03.874 --> 00:59:05.292
- That's right.
- You believe him?

1057
00:59:07.377 --> 00:59:09.796
Himmler ran the camps. right?

1058
00:59:09.880 --> 00:59:11.047
He was the head of the SS.

1059
00:59:11.131 --> 00:59:12.966
Göring was the head of the Air Force.

1060
00:59:13.049 --> 00:59:15.510
How often in America
does the head of the Air Force know

1061
00:59:15.594 --> 00:59:17.387
what the head
of the Secret Service is doing?

1062
00:59:17.471 --> 00:59:20.390
I'm sorry. but I cannot believe that
we're having this conversation right now.

1063
00:59:20.474 --> 00:59:22.184
- I'm doing what you asked.
- No!

1064
00:59:22.267 --> 00:59:24.311
- You're apologizing for him.
- JACKSON: Gentlemen. please.

1065
00:59:24.394 --> 00:59:26.772
- I'm not the one defending the Nazi.
- You think I'm defending him?

1066
00:59:26.855 --> 00:59:29.107
I am analyzing him. you provincial moron.

1067
00:59:30.776 --> 00:59:33.945
Göring is. above all things. a narcissist.

1068
00:59:34.738 --> 00:59:38.784
The only thing he cares about is building
Germany up and then becoming her leader.

1069
00:59:38.867 --> 00:59:40.619
He does not care about the Jews.

1070
00:59:40.702 --> 00:59:43.038
- So. he's fine with them dying.
- DOUGLAS: And he's fine with them not.

1071
00:59:43.121 --> 00:59:46.833
The only thing Hermann Göring cares about
is Hermann Göring.

1072
00:59:46.917 --> 00:59:49.836
Does that sound like a man
who dedicates himself

1073
00:59:49.920 --> 00:59:52.130
to the extermination of an entire race?

1074
00:59:55.801 --> 00:59:58.637
Well. Dr. Kelley. I really appreciate
your thoughtfulness on this.

1075
00:59:58.720 --> 01:00:00.639
but I have to admit. it is very hard...

1076
01:00:01.807 --> 01:00:02.808
to believe.

1077
01:00:04.643 --> 01:00:07.896
You wanna walk into that courtroom
with a handful of assumptions.

1078
01:00:08.814 --> 01:00:09.815
fine.

1079
01:00:11.191 --> 01:00:12.901
But he will eat you for breakfast.

1080
01:00:16.863 --> 01:00:19.491
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

1081
01:00:23.036 --> 01:00:25.997
[LEY SPEAKING GERMAN]

1082
01:00:26.081 --> 01:00:28.416
[IN ENGLISH] "I would like to apologize
for my outburst earlier.

1083
01:00:28.500 --> 01:00:29.793
"I'm feeling much better."

1084
01:00:31.503 --> 01:00:32.671
That's good. Dr. Ley.

1085
01:00:33.839 --> 01:00:34.840
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1086
01:00:38.093 --> 01:00:40.470
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "And. you?
Something seems to be troubling you."

1087
01:00:43.557 --> 01:00:44.599
I'm fine.

1088
01:00:46.393 --> 01:00:48.812
- [SPEAKING GERMAN]
- [LEY SPEAKING GERMAN]

1089
01:00:50.856 --> 01:00:51.857
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "Don't worry."

1090
01:00:51.940 --> 01:00:52.941
[LEY SPEAKING GERMAN]

1091
01:00:55.902 --> 01:00:57.487
HOWIE: [IN ENGLISH] "This will all
be over soon."

1092
01:00:57.571 --> 01:00:59.322
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1093
01:01:03.994 --> 01:01:06.121
DOUGLAS: <i>Ley's mood is markedly improved.</i>

1094
01:01:07.038 --> 01:01:10.584
<i>He told us he has begun
making arrangements for his defense.</i>

1095
01:01:11.626 --> 01:01:15.672
<i>I feel as though. for the first time.
he's reached out to me.</i>

1096
01:01:15.755 --> 01:01:18.216
[ALARM BLARING]

1097
01:01:18.300 --> 01:01:19.634
Oh. shit.

1098
01:01:20.302 --> 01:01:21.386
SOLDIER: Hurry! Move!

1099
01:01:21.469 --> 01:01:22.637
Doc! Come quick!

1100
01:01:22.721 --> 01:01:25.223
[ALARM CONTINUES BLARING]

1101
01:01:25.307 --> 01:01:27.809
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1102
01:01:27.893 --> 01:01:29.644
[GROANING] Jesus!

1103
01:01:30.812 --> 01:01:35.025
[DOUGLAS PANTING]

1104
01:01:36.568 --> 01:01:38.945
ANDRUS: Ripped out the hem of his towel
to make a rope.

1105
01:01:40.655 --> 01:01:43.658
Stuffed his underwear into his mouth
so he wouldn't scream and then...

1106
01:01:45.827 --> 01:01:47.621
just leaned forward.

1107
01:01:47.704 --> 01:01:49.915
Apparently. with a great deal
of determination.

1108
01:01:51.458 --> 01:01:52.709
You didn't see any of this coming?

1109
01:01:53.209 --> 01:01:54.586
He told me he was doing better.

1110
01:01:56.713 --> 01:01:57.797
"Told you"?

1111
01:02:00.091 --> 01:02:01.509
You're supposed to keep them alive.

1112
01:02:02.677 --> 01:02:05.138
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1113
01:02:12.312 --> 01:02:14.147
ANDRUS: I'm bringing in another doctor.

1114
01:02:14.230 --> 01:02:17.609
It's been determined a second opinion
is required for some of your patients.

1115
01:02:19.277 --> 01:02:21.363
Dr. Gilbert arrives this afternoon.

1116
01:02:22.030 --> 01:02:23.198
You will brief him.

1117
01:02:29.412 --> 01:02:31.498
How do you feel about suicide?

1118
01:02:37.128 --> 01:02:39.506
The last refuge of cowards. yeah.

1119
01:02:41.508 --> 01:02:44.010
Or the last act of a desperate man?

1120
01:02:45.929 --> 01:02:48.056
There are always exceptions. of course.

1121
01:02:52.102 --> 01:02:54.813
[INHALES] You are in trouble.

1122
01:02:55.397 --> 01:02:56.523
Why would you say that?

1123
01:02:56.606 --> 01:02:59.609
New doctor. New tests.

1124
01:02:59.693 --> 01:03:02.779
Since Ley died. they no longer trust you.

1125
01:03:03.697 --> 01:03:04.781
You're wrong.

1126
01:03:05.949 --> 01:03:08.201
[SIGHS] Douglas...

1127
01:03:09.869 --> 01:03:12.455
when you are in a position of power...

1128
01:03:14.791 --> 01:03:16.626
they will always come after you.

1129
01:03:17.502 --> 01:03:19.462
You have to protect yourself.

1130
01:03:19.546 --> 01:03:22.632
Why would I have to protect myself
from my allies?

1131
01:03:23.258 --> 01:03:28.680
Just because a man is your ally
does not mean he is on your side.

1132
01:03:29.806 --> 01:03:32.058
My father was a diplomat.
Did I tell you this?

1133
01:03:32.142 --> 01:03:33.143
- No.
- Ah.

1134
01:03:34.602 --> 01:03:35.937
[EXHALES]

1135
01:03:36.855 --> 01:03:37.856
Yeah.

1136
01:03:38.857 --> 01:03:42.736
He was... [SIGHS] ...posted to Africa.

1137
01:03:44.446 --> 01:03:47.657
And it was there he was
to meet his best friend.

1138
01:03:48.491 --> 01:03:52.912
A man named Hermann von Epstein.

1139
01:03:54.748 --> 01:03:56.541
I was named after him.

1140
01:03:59.753 --> 01:04:02.756
Yeah. I was named for a Jew.

1141
01:04:03.339 --> 01:04:04.340
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1142
01:04:04.424 --> 01:04:08.720
[INHALES] We loved Uncle Hermann so much.

1143
01:04:08.803 --> 01:04:11.681
He was very rich. [CHUCKLES]

1144
01:04:12.265 --> 01:04:15.310
He lived in Veldenstein Castle. [SIGHS]

1145
01:04:15.894 --> 01:04:18.021
And when I was six years old.

1146
01:04:19.814 --> 01:04:23.068
he moved my entire family in with him.

1147
01:04:24.402 --> 01:04:25.403
Can you imagine?

1148
01:04:26.446 --> 01:04:29.324
It was a child's dream
to live in such a castle.

1149
01:04:30.492 --> 01:04:34.079
I would run down the halls.
pretending I was a knight.

1150
01:04:35.205 --> 01:04:37.749
I would stare down from the battlements.

1151
01:04:37.832 --> 01:04:41.127
envisioning armies swarming to attack.

1152
01:04:42.670 --> 01:04:47.801
Uncle Hermann. he lived in the largest
and most beautiful room on the top floor.

1153
01:04:48.676 --> 01:04:52.222
Down the hall. my mother had a bedroom.
also beautiful.

1154
01:04:54.265 --> 01:04:55.475
My father...

1155
01:04:58.019 --> 01:05:00.522
he lived in a small bedroom
on the ground floor.

1156
01:05:02.774 --> 01:05:08.071
And I was to realize
just how rich Uncle Hermann was.

1157
01:05:09.280 --> 01:05:12.408
So rich that he could move my family in.

1158
01:05:13.660 --> 01:05:16.788
So rich that he could put my father
on the ground floor.

1159
01:05:19.332 --> 01:05:21.417
So rich that. whenever he wanted.

1160
01:05:23.002 --> 01:05:24.879
he could walk down the hall...

1161
01:05:28.007 --> 01:05:29.634
and enjoy my mother.

1162
01:05:32.846 --> 01:05:34.639
Just because a man is your ally

1163
01:05:36.015 --> 01:05:38.810
does not mean he is on your side.

1164
01:05:42.230 --> 01:05:45.275
[PAGES RUSTLING]

1165
01:05:47.193 --> 01:05:50.738
You found Hermann Göring
to be "imaginative"?

1166
01:05:50.822 --> 01:05:53.199
I didn't find him to be that way.
the test did.

1167
01:05:53.950 --> 01:05:56.369
Well. that is what
a second opinion is for.

1168
01:05:56.953 --> 01:06:02.041
[INHALES] Which... [SIGHS SOFTLY]
...brings us to Rudolf Hess.

1169
01:06:02.834 --> 01:06:07.213
[INHALES] I'm inclined to believe
that his amnesia is genuine.

1170
01:06:07.297 --> 01:06:09.674
You mean the part where he forgets
about being a Nazi?

1171
01:06:10.466 --> 01:06:12.260
Okay. Look. Dr. Kelley.

1172
01:06:13.178 --> 01:06:16.973
- I'm not here to step on your toes. okay?
- [SIGHS SOFTLY]

1173
01:06:17.056 --> 01:06:19.267
I'll share research. We'll co-author.

1174
01:06:20.476 --> 01:06:21.769
Co-author what?

1175
01:06:21.853 --> 01:06:25.106
You don't have to play coy with me.
We're both here for the same reason.

1176
01:06:26.566 --> 01:06:28.902
Now. two books
about the Nazi High Command.

1177
01:06:28.985 --> 01:06:30.612
that's gonna cut into the market.

1178
01:06:30.695 --> 01:06:32.697
I say we write it together.

1179
01:06:33.364 --> 01:06:35.909
- Hmm?
- Mm-hmm.

1180
01:06:39.329 --> 01:06:40.788
DOUGLAS: Good luck with your tests.

1181
01:06:46.002 --> 01:06:50.298
<i>[NOCTURNE OP. 9 NO. 2</i> BY CHOPIN
PLAYING ON PIANO]

1182
01:06:55.303 --> 01:06:56.304
<i>Doktor.</i>

1183
01:06:58.223 --> 01:06:59.891
- [GASPS]
- [SPEAKING GERMAN]

1184
01:07:01.059 --> 01:07:02.268
<i>Danke schön.</i>

1185
01:07:06.898 --> 01:07:08.233
[CONTINUES SPEAKING GERMAN]

1186
01:07:13.863 --> 01:07:17.700
[CONTINUES PLAYING ON PIANO]

1187
01:07:21.913 --> 01:07:24.916
[MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

1188
01:07:36.052 --> 01:07:38.263
[INAUDIBLE CONVERSATION]

1189
01:07:38.346 --> 01:07:42.600
- [INAUDIBLE]
- [MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

1190
01:07:53.695 --> 01:07:55.363
[COINS CLINKING]

1191
01:08:06.207 --> 01:08:07.208
[BOTH LAUGH]

1192
01:08:09.419 --> 01:08:10.670
HERMANN: She was surprised?

1193
01:08:10.753 --> 01:08:14.132
Oh. she was. uh. astounded.

1194
01:08:14.215 --> 01:08:15.341
Teach me this trick.

1195
01:08:16.217 --> 01:08:17.677
- The coin behind the ear?
- Yeah. yeah.

1196
01:08:17.760 --> 01:08:21.264
Teach me this trick.
so I too can astound her.

1197
01:08:22.348 --> 01:08:23.349
Hmm.

1198
01:08:24.017 --> 01:08:26.978
- I gave my silver dollar to your daughter.
- [SIGHING] Ah.

1199
01:08:27.770 --> 01:08:29.105
It's the simplest trick in the world.

1200
01:08:29.188 --> 01:08:31.774
It works because. you know.
people want to believe.

1201
01:08:32.442 --> 01:08:35.486
Well. you hold up the dollar.
and you say.

1202
01:08:35.570 --> 01:08:39.532
"Hey. folks! Here is an ordinary.
average silver dollar."

1203
01:08:41.451 --> 01:08:43.995
Then you put it in your other hand.
All right?

1204
01:08:45.455 --> 01:08:46.539
You focus on it.

1205
01:08:48.958 --> 01:08:51.252
But really. it's right here.

1206
01:08:51.336 --> 01:08:52.962
[GASPS]

1207
01:08:53.046 --> 01:08:55.089
You palm it in your right hand.

1208
01:08:55.173 --> 01:08:56.799
- Palm it.
- Yeah.

1209
01:08:56.883 --> 01:08:59.719
- You keep it between these two fingers...
- [HERMANN SIGHS SOFTLY]

1210
01:08:59.802 --> 01:09:01.512
DOUGLAS: ...and you wrap your palm
around it.

1211
01:09:01.596 --> 01:09:03.473
but you focus on your left hand.

1212
01:09:06.100 --> 01:09:09.187
And you feel the coin in there.
the weight of it. Right?

1213
01:09:09.270 --> 01:09:13.232
And if you believe it.
then they'll believe it.

1214
01:09:15.276 --> 01:09:19.864
And then. you just.
well. you reach behind the ear... [GASPS]

1215
01:09:20.448 --> 01:09:24.535
- Abracadabra!
- [LAUGHS. SIGHS] Hmm.

1216
01:09:26.913 --> 01:09:28.206
What is "abracadabra"?

1217
01:09:28.706 --> 01:09:30.291
Uh. it's the magic words.

1218
01:09:30.375 --> 01:09:33.044
It. uh. gives the illusion. uh...

1219
01:09:33.127 --> 01:09:35.338
[INHALES] ...a cosmic weight.

1220
01:09:35.922 --> 01:09:38.341
And it always must be "abracadabra"?

1221
01:09:38.424 --> 01:09:40.343
No. no. It could be anything.

1222
01:09:40.426 --> 01:09:42.428
It could be "presto."

1223
01:09:44.305 --> 01:09:46.182
- I think I prefer "abracadabra."
- [SNICKERING]

1224
01:09:46.265 --> 01:09:48.643
So. it was your father
who taught you this trick?

1225
01:09:48.726 --> 01:09:51.562
Uh... my father? No.

1226
01:09:53.231 --> 01:09:55.566
You say that like it is unthinkable.

1227
01:09:56.401 --> 01:09:57.735
Yeah. my father was content

1228
01:09:57.819 --> 01:10:02.573
to ply his trade
and display a cheerful disposition.

1229
01:10:04.951 --> 01:10:06.869
He was a man of no accomplishment.

1230
01:10:07.453 --> 01:10:08.704
But you believe...

1231
01:10:10.706 --> 01:10:12.291
you are destined for more.

1232
01:10:14.252 --> 01:10:16.421
You want to be known as a great man.

1233
01:10:22.468 --> 01:10:23.469
Yes.

1234
01:10:23.553 --> 01:10:25.638
And I am your ticket.

1235
01:10:27.640 --> 01:10:28.975
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1236
01:10:29.058 --> 01:10:32.353
You will return to America
as the great scholar of the Nazis.

1237
01:10:33.771 --> 01:10:38.025
and I will have a trick
to impress my daughter

1238
01:10:38.943 --> 01:10:40.445
when this trial is done.

1239
01:10:41.988 --> 01:10:43.156
[SIGHS SOFTLY]

1240
01:10:47.243 --> 01:10:48.870
You stopped taking me with you to see him.

1241
01:10:48.953 --> 01:10:50.121
[DOOR CLOSES]

1242
01:10:53.082 --> 01:10:54.625
Didn't want to bother you so late.

1243
01:10:56.169 --> 01:10:58.004
You've been seeing him a lot without me.

1244
01:10:59.130 --> 01:11:00.339
What're you doing. Doc?

1245
01:11:02.258 --> 01:11:03.593
Trying to learn something.

1246
01:11:04.927 --> 01:11:06.637
You sure that's what this is still about?

1247
01:11:10.308 --> 01:11:11.350
Good night. Howie.

1248
01:11:16.063 --> 01:11:17.356
[GATE CLANKING]

1249
01:11:19.025 --> 01:11:20.860
[INHALES. EXHALES]

1250
01:11:21.903 --> 01:11:23.946
How are you gonna
defend yourself. Hermann?

1251
01:11:24.030 --> 01:11:25.573
HERMANN: Oh. [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1252
01:11:26.115 --> 01:11:28.409
- Would not you like to know?
- DOUGLAS: I'm serious.

1253
01:11:32.914 --> 01:11:34.123
Are we friends. Doctor?

1254
01:11:36.375 --> 01:11:40.421
I think that word is a little too simple
for what we are.

1255
01:11:41.088 --> 01:11:42.256
[GULPS]

1256
01:11:43.132 --> 01:11:44.675
But are you asking me this...

1257
01:11:46.344 --> 01:11:47.428
as a friend?

1258
01:11:50.681 --> 01:11:51.682
I am.

1259
01:11:56.521 --> 01:12:00.691
[SIGHS SOFTLY] Tomorrow
when I enter my plea.

1260
01:12:02.693 --> 01:12:04.237
I will read a statement.

1261
01:12:05.154 --> 01:12:06.405
I am going to say

1262
01:12:07.615 --> 01:12:11.452
that I assume all responsibility
for my actions.

1263
01:12:11.536 --> 01:12:12.912
I will refuse. however.

1264
01:12:13.704 --> 01:12:17.458
to accept responsibility
for acts committed by others

1265
01:12:17.542 --> 01:12:18.876
that I was unaware of.

1266
01:12:20.461 --> 01:12:22.421
and I would not have approved of.

1267
01:12:25.841 --> 01:12:26.926
What I did...

1268
01:12:30.179 --> 01:12:31.556
I did for my country.

1269
01:12:33.349 --> 01:12:35.434
Tell me you would not do the same
for yours.

1270
01:12:53.828 --> 01:12:56.664
- They told me I could find you here.
- [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1271
01:13:00.543 --> 01:13:02.169
In seven hours...

1272
01:13:04.547 --> 01:13:07.508
the whole world is going to be focused
on this room.

1273
01:13:09.552 --> 01:13:10.678
This is it.

1274
01:13:11.887 --> 01:13:12.930
This is everything.

1275
01:13:19.687 --> 01:13:23.065
This is the statement
that Göring plans on reading tomorrow.

1276
01:13:30.281 --> 01:13:31.365
Thank you.

1277
01:13:31.449 --> 01:13:33.951
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1278
01:13:45.963 --> 01:13:51.761
[THUMPS]

1279
01:13:51.844 --> 01:13:53.512
- [LEVER CRANKING]
- [ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

1280
01:13:53.596 --> 01:13:55.848
[FILM ROLL SQUEAKING]

1281
01:13:55.931 --> 01:13:58.934
[MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

1282
01:14:04.106 --> 01:14:05.399
[HERMANN SPEAKING GERMAN]

1283
01:14:10.863 --> 01:14:13.282
[CONTINUES SPEAKING GERMAN]

1284
01:14:25.044 --> 01:14:26.420
SOLDIER: [IN ENGLISH] Atten-hut!

1285
01:14:33.427 --> 01:14:34.428
Let's go.

1286
01:14:35.763 --> 01:14:38.432
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1287
01:14:40.810 --> 01:14:43.688
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1288
01:14:50.444 --> 01:14:51.445
MAN: [IN ENGLISH] Here they come!

1289
01:14:51.529 --> 01:14:54.156
[RHYTHMIC THUMPING]

1290
01:14:56.117 --> 01:14:57.076
DOUGLAS: Jesus!

1291
01:14:57.159 --> 01:14:59.370
[THUMPING INTENSIFIES]

1292
01:15:02.957 --> 01:15:04.709
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1293
01:15:08.754 --> 01:15:11.757
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1294
01:15:17.555 --> 01:15:18.723
[DOOR CLOSES]

1295
01:15:18.806 --> 01:15:20.474
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1296
01:15:22.435 --> 01:15:25.479
[ELEVATOR DOOR WHIRRING]

1297
01:15:27.398 --> 01:15:31.986
[CAMERAS FLASHING]

1298
01:15:32.069 --> 01:15:35.072
[MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

1299
01:15:38.743 --> 01:15:41.245
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1300
01:15:43.289 --> 01:15:46.751
[CAMERAS FLASHING]

1301
01:16:00.973 --> 01:16:02.808
[LIGHTS TRILLING]

1302
01:16:02.892 --> 01:16:03.934
BAILIFF: All rise!

1303
01:16:11.734 --> 01:16:14.528
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1304
01:16:40.930 --> 01:16:42.640
[SIGHS]

1305
01:16:48.646 --> 01:16:49.980
May it please Your Honors...

1306
01:16:53.526 --> 01:16:57.696
The privilege of opening the first trial
in history

1307
01:16:58.531 --> 01:17:01.033
for crimes against the peace
of the world

1308
01:17:01.116 --> 01:17:03.619
imposes a grave responsibility.

1309
01:17:05.704 --> 01:17:08.916
The wrongs which we seek
to condemn and punish

1310
01:17:09.959 --> 01:17:11.502
have been so calculated...

1311
01:17:12.545 --> 01:17:15.089
[OVER SPEAKERS] <i>...so malignant.
and so devastating</i>

1312
01:17:16.048 --> 01:17:19.844
that civilization cannot tolerate
their being ignored.

1313
01:17:21.178 --> 01:17:24.056
because we cannot survive
their being repeated.

1314
01:17:27.268 --> 01:17:31.522
In the prisoners' dock
sit 20-odd broken men.

1315
01:17:32.773 --> 01:17:37.486
We will show them to be living symbols
of racial hatred.

1316
01:17:39.071 --> 01:17:41.740
of terrorism and violence.

1317
01:17:43.325 --> 01:17:48.122
and of the arrogance and cruelty of power.

1318
01:17:50.165 --> 01:17:52.668
[OVER RADIO] <i>Civilization
can afford no compromise</i>

1319
01:17:53.669 --> 01:17:56.922
<i>by dealing ambiguously or indecisively.</i>

1320
01:17:57.006 --> 01:18:02.511
with the men in whom these forces
now precariously survive.

1321
01:18:07.558 --> 01:18:09.727
Wars are no longer local.

1322
01:18:12.062 --> 01:18:17.067
All modern wars become world wars.
eventually.

1323
01:18:19.612 --> 01:18:22.698
And none of the big nations can stay out.

1324
01:18:24.366 --> 01:18:29.622
But the ultimate step
in avoiding periodic wars

1325
01:18:29.705 --> 01:18:32.666
in a system of international lawlessness

1326
01:18:34.168 --> 01:18:38.130
is to make statesmen
responsible for the law!

1327
01:18:40.841 --> 01:18:42.384
And let me make clear

1328
01:18:42.468 --> 01:18:46.221
that while this law is first applied
against German aggressors.

1329
01:18:46.305 --> 01:18:49.224
it must condemn aggression
by any other nation

1330
01:18:49.308 --> 01:18:51.810
including those who sit here now.
in judgement.

1331
01:18:53.312 --> 01:18:58.317
We are able to do away
with domestic tyranny

1332
01:18:58.400 --> 01:19:00.361
and violence and aggression

1333
01:19:00.444 --> 01:19:03.238
by those in power against the rights
of their own people...

1334
01:19:04.907 --> 01:19:07.368
only when we make all men

1335
01:19:08.744 --> 01:19:10.913
answerable to the law.

1336
01:19:25.427 --> 01:19:26.595
JUDGE LAWRENCE: Hermann Göring.

1337
01:19:29.223 --> 01:19:33.769
The defendants are to plead guilty
or not guilty to the charges against them.

1338
01:19:34.728 --> 01:19:39.650
They will proceed. in turn. to a point
in the dock opposite to the microphone.

1339
01:19:53.205 --> 01:19:54.999
I am Hermann Wilhelm Göring.

1340
01:19:55.082 --> 01:19:57.292
- [GAVEL BANGS]
- I stand before the Court today...

1341
01:19:57.376 --> 01:19:59.253
- [GAVEL BANGING]
- HERMANN: ...and the world...

1342
01:19:59.336 --> 01:20:00.629
[OVER RADIO] <i>...and pledge
only to tell...</i>

1343
01:20:00.713 --> 01:20:02.423
[GAVEL BANGING]

1344
01:20:03.090 --> 01:20:04.842
JUDGE LAWRENCE: The Tribunal
has reached the decision

1345
01:20:05.426 --> 01:20:08.929
that the defendants are not entitled
to make a statement.

1346
01:20:10.014 --> 01:20:13.726
They will be permitted to address
the Court prior to their sentencing.

1347
01:20:16.562 --> 01:20:18.063
As <i>Reichsmarschall</i> of Germany...

1348
01:20:18.147 --> 01:20:20.065
You are not <i>Reichsmarschall</i> here.

1349
01:20:21.108 --> 01:20:23.902
You are only Hermann Göring. the prisoner.

1350
01:20:24.570 --> 01:20:27.489
Do you plead guilty or not guilty?

1351
01:20:33.454 --> 01:20:34.913
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1352
01:20:36.415 --> 01:20:38.000
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

1353
01:20:38.083 --> 01:20:40.961
- [BREATH TREMBLING]
- [CLICKS]

1354
01:20:47.384 --> 01:20:50.345
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1355
01:20:50.429 --> 01:20:52.598
[ENGINE WHIRRING]

1356
01:21:04.151 --> 01:21:05.152
Emmy!

1357
01:21:06.487 --> 01:21:07.488
Edda!

1358
01:21:08.906 --> 01:21:09.907
Emmy!

1359
01:21:11.658 --> 01:21:14.286
What happened? What happened?
Where are they?

1360
01:21:14.369 --> 01:21:15.621
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1361
01:21:15.704 --> 01:21:17.247
[IN ENGLISH] What? Where are they?

1362
01:21:17.331 --> 01:21:18.749
- They took them!
- Who?

1363
01:21:19.708 --> 01:21:20.959
Americans!

1364
01:21:23.545 --> 01:21:26.548
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1365
01:21:29.718 --> 01:21:33.430
[ENGINE STARTS. ACCELERATING]

1366
01:21:35.933 --> 01:21:36.934
DOUGLAS: Emmy!

1367
01:21:37.935 --> 01:21:39.603
Emmy! Edda!

1368
01:21:41.855 --> 01:21:43.190
Emmy. Edda.

1369
01:21:44.358 --> 01:21:46.151
Emmy! Emmy Göring!

1370
01:21:47.444 --> 01:21:49.822
[PANTING]

1371
01:21:51.365 --> 01:21:53.617
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]
- ANDRUS: Yeah?

1372
01:21:56.578 --> 01:21:59.998
I need a favor. [PANTING]

1373
01:22:00.082 --> 01:22:01.208
You gotta be shitting me.

1374
01:22:02.543 --> 01:22:03.877
Thanks. I'm gonna need it.

1375
01:22:05.671 --> 01:22:07.798
[SIGHS] They've arrested Emmy Göring

1376
01:22:08.382 --> 01:22:11.301
on suspicion of complicity
with her husband's art thefts.

1377
01:22:11.385 --> 01:22:13.595
Kid goes to the nuns. No contact allowed.

1378
01:22:14.221 --> 01:22:15.430
They're women and children.

1379
01:22:16.598 --> 01:22:17.683
Yeah.

1380
01:22:18.851 --> 01:22:20.269
Sir. we're supposed to be
better than this.

1381
01:22:20.352 --> 01:22:21.812
It's out of my hands!

1382
01:22:23.397 --> 01:22:24.398
And you're welcome.

1383
01:22:28.277 --> 01:22:29.319
By the way.

1384
01:22:30.070 --> 01:22:31.488
how did you know where she was hiding?

1385
01:22:34.533 --> 01:22:35.617
[SIGHS SOFTLY]

1386
01:22:36.910 --> 01:22:37.995
[HERMANN SIGHS]

1387
01:22:40.289 --> 01:22:41.415
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1388
01:22:43.625 --> 01:22:45.127
Did Edda play for you again?

1389
01:22:48.338 --> 01:22:50.174
- She did.
- Ah.

1390
01:22:51.175 --> 01:22:52.551
She's very talented.

1391
01:22:53.177 --> 01:22:54.428
She likes you.

1392
01:22:57.181 --> 01:22:58.765
Do you have their letters?

1393
01:22:59.516 --> 01:23:00.517
[INHALES]

1394
01:23:00.601 --> 01:23:01.602
[SMACKS LIPS] No.

1395
01:23:02.603 --> 01:23:05.105
No letters. unfortunately.

1396
01:23:05.189 --> 01:23:06.190
No?

1397
01:23:07.441 --> 01:23:08.442
Next time.

1398
01:23:09.193 --> 01:23:11.403
[LOCKS CLICKING. DOOR CREAKING]

1399
01:23:13.989 --> 01:23:15.449
And here's my new doctor.

1400
01:23:16.325 --> 01:23:18.368
We were just talking about my family.

1401
01:23:18.452 --> 01:23:21.121
Ah. yes. Well. I was sorry
to hear about that.

1402
01:23:23.457 --> 01:23:24.666
About what?

1403
01:23:24.750 --> 01:23:26.043
Their arrest.

1404
01:23:26.126 --> 01:23:29.046
Your wife and daughter were arrested
five days ago.

1405
01:23:30.756 --> 01:23:31.882
He didn't tell you?

1406
01:23:37.638 --> 01:23:38.639
DOUGLAS: Hey.

1407
01:23:38.722 --> 01:23:40.390
Hey! What the hell was that?

1408
01:23:41.058 --> 01:23:45.145
That was me being honest with my patient.
something you oughta try sometime.

1409
01:23:45.229 --> 01:23:46.730
You destroyed him in there.

1410
01:23:46.813 --> 01:23:47.814
So?

1411
01:23:47.898 --> 01:23:49.942
- [GRUNTS]
- [THUDS]

1412
01:23:50.025 --> 01:23:52.611
[GRUNTS] What the hell is wrong with you?
What's wrong with you. hmm?

1413
01:23:52.694 --> 01:23:54.446
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1414
01:23:54.529 --> 01:23:56.406
SOLDIER 1 : Hey. stop!
SOLDIER 2: Hey. stop!

1415
01:23:56.490 --> 01:23:57.741
[ALL GRUNTING]

1416
01:23:57.824 --> 01:24:00.994
Jesus Christ.
You're mental health professionals!

1417
01:24:01.536 --> 01:24:02.788
For Christ's sake!

1418
01:24:06.667 --> 01:24:10.254
Dr. Gilbert. would you like me to place
Dr. Kelley under arrest?

1419
01:24:14.841 --> 01:24:17.302
- No. sir.
- Then get out of my goddamn office!

1420
01:24:18.887 --> 01:24:21.056
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1421
01:24:22.140 --> 01:24:24.434
- [LAUGHING] Cinema.
- [ALL LAUGHING]

1422
01:24:25.435 --> 01:24:27.562
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1423
01:24:28.397 --> 01:24:29.439
BAILIFF: [IN ENGLISH] All rise!

1424
01:24:43.912 --> 01:24:45.247
May it please the Court.

1425
01:24:45.330 --> 01:24:49.543
the prosecution would now like to enter
into evidence the following film footage.

1426
01:24:50.002 --> 01:24:54.464
The images you are about to see have
never before been shown in public.

1427
01:24:55.173 --> 01:24:57.801
This film should offer a brief explanation

1428
01:24:58.760 --> 01:25:02.014
of what the words
"concentration camp" implied.

1429
01:25:07.060 --> 01:25:08.061
[SWITCH CLICKS]

1430
01:25:10.814 --> 01:25:12.983
[WHIRRING]

1431
01:25:17.946 --> 01:25:21.908
NARRATOR: <i>These are the locations of
the largest concentration and prison camps</i>

1432
01:25:21.992 --> 01:25:25.912
<i>maintained throughout Germany
and occupied Europe under the Nazi regime.</i>

1433
01:25:28.874 --> 01:25:31.043
<i>The 4th Armored Division
of General Patton's Third Army</i>

1434
01:25:31.126 --> 01:25:33.003
<i>liberated this camp early in April.</i>

1435
01:25:34.296 --> 01:25:35.964
[BREATH TREMBLING]

1436
01:25:36.048 --> 01:25:39.426
NARRATOR: <i>They see the woodshed where
lime-covered bodies are stacked in layers</i>

1437
01:25:39.509 --> 01:25:41.261
<i>and the stench is overpowering.</i>

1438
01:25:51.063 --> 01:25:53.106
<i>Slave labor camp at Nordhausen</i>

1439
01:25:53.190 --> 01:25:55.901
<i>liberated by the 3rd Armored Division.
First Army.</i>

1440
01:25:55.984 --> 01:25:58.612
<i>At least 3.000 political prisoners
died here</i>

1441
01:25:58.695 --> 01:26:01.698
<i>at the brutal hands of SS troops
and pardoned German criminals</i>

1442
01:26:01.782 --> 01:26:03.283
<i>who were the camp guard.</i>

1443
01:26:03.367 --> 01:26:05.202
<i>Nordhausen had been a depository</i>

1444
01:26:05.285 --> 01:26:09.122
<i>for slaves found unfit for work
in the underground V-bomb plants</i>

1445
01:26:09.206 --> 01:26:11.375
<i>and in other German camps and factories.</i>

1446
01:26:16.338 --> 01:26:19.508
<i>Amid the corpses are human skeletons
too weak to move.</i>

1447
01:26:24.221 --> 01:26:26.932
<i>Men of our medical battalions
worked two days and nights</i>

1448
01:26:27.015 --> 01:26:29.184
<i>binding wounds and giving medications.</i>

1449
01:26:29.267 --> 01:26:32.062
<i>But for advanced cases
of starvation and tuberculosis.</i>

1450
01:26:32.145 --> 01:26:34.106
<i>there were often no cures.</i>

1451
01:26:34.856 --> 01:26:38.610
<i>The survivors are shown being evacuated
for treatment in Allied hospitals.</i>

1452
01:26:40.487 --> 01:26:43.031
- [INAUDIBLE]
- [PROJECTOR CONTINUES WHIRRING]

1453
01:26:51.456 --> 01:26:54.668
<i>I'm Lieutenant Senior Grade
Jack H. Taylor. US Navy.</i>

1454
01:26:54.751 --> 01:26:56.086
<i>from Hollywood. California.</i>

1455
01:26:56.169 --> 01:26:59.131
<i>Believe it or not. this is the first time
I've ever been in the movies.</i>

1456
01:26:59.214 --> 01:27:01.466
<i>I was captured December 1st.</i>

1457
01:27:02.342 --> 01:27:05.554
<i>I was taken to this
Mauthausen Concentration Lager.</i>

1458
01:27:06.179 --> 01:27:08.098
<i>an extermination camp.</i>

1459
01:27:08.974 --> 01:27:15.689
<i>where we have been starving
and... and beaten and killed.</i>

1460
01:27:16.314 --> 01:27:19.067
<i>Uh. fortunately. my turn hadn't come.</i>

1461
01:27:20.026 --> 01:27:23.947
<i>Uh... there were...</i>

1462
01:27:24.030 --> 01:27:25.365
INTERVIEWER: <i>How many ways
do they execute?</i>

1463
01:27:26.199 --> 01:27:27.200
<i>Five or six ways.</i>

1464
01:27:27.284 --> 01:27:30.412
<i>By gas. by shooting. by beating.</i>

1465
01:27:30.495 --> 01:27:31.997
<i>That is. beating with clubs.</i>

1466
01:27:32.747 --> 01:27:33.915
<i>Uh...</i>

1467
01:27:35.041 --> 01:27:37.377
<i>By exposure.</i>

1468
01:27:38.128 --> 01:27:40.839
<i>That is. standing out in the snow
naked for 48 hours</i>

1469
01:27:40.922 --> 01:27:44.593
<i>and having cold water thrown on them
in the middle of winter.</i>

1470
01:27:44.676 --> 01:27:45.802
<i>Starvation.</i>

1471
01:27:47.220 --> 01:27:48.305
<i>Dogs.</i>

1472
01:27:48.388 --> 01:27:50.974
<i>And pushing over a 100-foot cliff.</i>

1473
01:27:52.767 --> 01:27:56.229
<i>This is all true. has been seen.
and is now being recorded.</i>

1474
01:28:01.359 --> 01:28:03.778
NARRATOR: <i>Nationalities and prison numbers
are tattooed</i>

1475
01:28:03.862 --> 01:28:05.614
<i>on the stomachs of the inmates.</i>

1476
01:28:14.289 --> 01:28:15.290
<i>In the official report.</i>

1477
01:28:15.373 --> 01:28:18.793
<i>the Buchenwald camp is termed
an extermination factory.</i>

1478
01:28:20.086 --> 01:28:23.882
<i>Bodies stacked one upon the other
were found outside the crematory.</i>

1479
01:28:27.052 --> 01:28:28.887
<i>A body disposal plant.</i>

1480
01:28:28.970 --> 01:28:31.473
<i>Inside are the ovens
which gave the crematorium</i>

1481
01:28:31.556 --> 01:28:35.977
<i>a maximum disposal capacity
of about 400 bodies per 10-hour day.</i>

1482
01:28:38.396 --> 01:28:39.731
[BREATH TREMBLING]

1483
01:28:39.814 --> 01:28:41.608
NARRATOR: <i>Dachau. near München.</i>

1484
01:28:41.691 --> 01:28:43.818
<i>one of the oldest
of the Nazi prison camps.</i>

1485
01:28:59.960 --> 01:29:03.338
<i>This is what the liberators found
inside the buildings.</i>

1486
01:29:29.489 --> 01:29:32.075
<i>Hanging in orderly rows
were the clothes of prisoners</i>

1487
01:29:32.158 --> 01:29:34.536
<i>who had been suffocated
in a lethal gas chamber.</i>

1488
01:29:35.704 --> 01:29:38.206
<i>They had been persuaded
to remove their clothing</i>

1489
01:29:38.290 --> 01:29:42.961
<i>under the pretext of taking a shower.
for which towels and soap were provided.</i>

1490
01:29:45.422 --> 01:29:47.048
[PROJECTOR WHIRRING]

1491
01:29:48.675 --> 01:29:50.969
<i>Sanitary conditions were so appalling</i>

1492
01:29:51.052 --> 01:29:54.806
<i>that heavy equipment had to be brought in
to speed the work of cleaning up.</i>

1493
01:30:07.110 --> 01:30:08.528
[CHAIR SCRAPING]

1494
01:30:16.244 --> 01:30:18.455
<i>This was Bergen-Belsen.</i>

1495
01:30:34.846 --> 01:30:36.056
[CELL DOOR SLAMS]

1496
01:30:46.483 --> 01:30:47.776
How's that possible?

1497
01:30:54.240 --> 01:30:55.450
[HERMANN SIGHS]

1498
01:30:58.370 --> 01:30:59.621
What I just saw.

1499
01:31:05.460 --> 01:31:06.711
How is it possible?

1500
01:31:07.837 --> 01:31:08.838
[INHALES SHARPLY]

1501
01:31:10.298 --> 01:31:11.424
Himmler.

1502
01:31:12.133 --> 01:31:13.843
Himmler wasn't second-in-command.

1503
01:31:14.844 --> 01:31:15.845
You were.

1504
01:31:16.471 --> 01:31:17.847
1.200 camps?

1505
01:31:18.682 --> 01:31:21.059
No. What am I supposed to believe.
that you didn't know?

1506
01:31:21.142 --> 01:31:22.769
Anyone can fake an atrocity.

1507
01:31:22.852 --> 01:31:25.438
So. you're saying the film was a fake.
That's your defense?

1508
01:31:25.522 --> 01:31:26.564
What would you have me say?

1509
01:31:26.648 --> 01:31:28.483
How about the truth for once?

1510
01:31:28.566 --> 01:31:29.567
Why?

1511
01:31:30.402 --> 01:31:32.028
So you can run and tell Jackson?

1512
01:31:33.738 --> 01:31:35.115
My friend.

1513
01:31:36.700 --> 01:31:38.201
your hypocrisy is stunning.

1514
01:31:39.202 --> 01:31:40.203
My hypocrisy?

1515
01:31:40.286 --> 01:31:42.622
You think American bullets and bombs
don't kill people?

1516
01:31:43.248 --> 01:31:47.752
You vaporize 150.000 Japanese
at the touch of a button.

1517
01:31:47.836 --> 01:31:51.506
and you presume to stand in judgement
on me for war crimes?

1518
01:31:51.589 --> 01:31:53.091
We had every right to defend ourselves.

1519
01:31:53.174 --> 01:31:55.760
How do you defend yourself
on someone else's soil?

1520
01:31:55.844 --> 01:31:58.304
There's a difference
between us bombing war factories

1521
01:31:58.388 --> 01:32:00.932
and civilians dying as collateral damage.

1522
01:32:01.015 --> 01:32:04.477
and you building
1.200 human slaughterhouses

1523
01:32:04.561 --> 01:32:07.731
designed to exterminate an entire race.

1524
01:32:07.814 --> 01:32:09.816
and you know it!

1525
01:32:09.899 --> 01:32:11.651
HERMANN: What do you think war is?

1526
01:32:15.363 --> 01:32:16.406
Not what I saw today.

1527
01:32:16.489 --> 01:32:19.909
What do you think the Russians do
to German prisoners of war?

1528
01:32:19.993 --> 01:32:22.704
You have your freedom.
and I am a prisoner

1529
01:32:22.787 --> 01:32:25.206
because you won. and we lost.

1530
01:32:25.290 --> 01:32:27.667
Not because you are morally superior!

1531
01:32:28.543 --> 01:32:31.838
This trial will be a farce in 15 years.

1532
01:32:31.921 --> 01:32:34.841
Great conquerors are not thought of
as murderers.

1533
01:32:35.508 --> 01:32:37.594
Genghis Khan. Alexander the Great...

1534
01:32:37.677 --> 01:32:39.721
You are not Alexander the Great!

1535
01:32:41.681 --> 01:32:44.184
You are a fat man in a cell.

1536
01:32:46.352 --> 01:32:47.771
And you knew.

1537
01:32:48.605 --> 01:32:49.814
HERMANN: Hmm.

1538
01:32:52.400 --> 01:32:54.569
I have made a mistake.

1539
01:32:58.948 --> 01:33:00.658
You are not destined for more.

1540
01:33:02.202 --> 01:33:05.955
You will have an unhappy life. I think.

1541
01:33:08.500 --> 01:33:10.919
It will all be overshadowed by this.

1542
01:33:12.212 --> 01:33:13.797
by the time spent with me.

1543
01:33:15.173 --> 01:33:17.967
You will write your volumes.
try to re-live it.

1544
01:33:18.968 --> 01:33:20.845
The one moment in your life

1545
01:33:22.347 --> 01:33:24.432
when you actually stood with greatness.

1546
01:33:25.016 --> 01:33:26.643
You think you're a great man?

1547
01:33:29.896 --> 01:33:31.356
You think that's your legacy?

1548
01:33:31.981 --> 01:33:33.483
HERMANN: At least I will have one.

1549
01:33:34.317 --> 01:33:37.111
You will leave no mark on this world.

1550
01:33:38.196 --> 01:33:39.823
I am the book!

1551
01:33:39.906 --> 01:33:42.617
You are merely a footnote.

1552
01:33:42.992 --> 01:33:43.993
[DOUGLAS SCOFFS]

1553
01:33:47.705 --> 01:33:49.332
They are gonna kill you.

1554
01:33:51.292 --> 01:33:52.836
They are gonna hang you

1555
01:33:53.670 --> 01:33:56.506
by the neck till you piss yourself...

1556
01:33:57.674 --> 01:33:58.675
and die.

1557
01:34:01.553 --> 01:34:02.804
Your wife will be a widow.

1558
01:34:04.514 --> 01:34:06.516
Your daughter will be an orphan.

1559
01:34:09.936 --> 01:34:11.980
And you will have done that to yourself.

1560
01:34:18.778 --> 01:34:19.779
[BANGING ON DOOR]

1561
01:34:29.539 --> 01:34:30.957
[CELL DOOR SLAMS]

1562
01:34:31.040 --> 01:34:33.042
[JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING]

1563
01:34:42.051 --> 01:34:43.052
[MATCHSTICK SIZZLES]

1564
01:34:44.679 --> 01:34:46.055
I know who you are.

1565
01:34:47.682 --> 01:34:49.017
What's he like?

1566
01:34:49.684 --> 01:34:50.727
You don't wanna know.

1567
01:34:51.686 --> 01:34:53.897
Jackson's putting him on the stand
day after tomorrow.

1568
01:34:53.980 --> 01:34:54.981
DOUGLAS: Hmm.

1569
01:34:56.274 --> 01:34:58.860
Jackson's gonna get killed.

1570
01:34:59.444 --> 01:35:00.862
Why do you say that?

1571
01:35:02.196 --> 01:35:05.033
Because Göring is ready for him.

1572
01:35:07.994 --> 01:35:09.621
He was ready for all of us.

1573
01:35:13.875 --> 01:35:18.087
Why don't you tell me all about it?

1574
01:35:19.881 --> 01:35:21.966
- [GLASSES CLINKING]
- ANDRUS: Look at that.

1575
01:35:22.050 --> 01:35:25.929
Your private conversations
with Hermann Göring made the front page.

1576
01:35:26.012 --> 01:35:27.430
- Sir. I...
- ANDRUS: You're finished.

1577
01:35:28.598 --> 01:35:30.808
I signed your transfer order this morning.

1578
01:35:30.892 --> 01:35:33.478
You're to be sent back to the States
where you'll be discharged.

1579
01:35:34.228 --> 01:35:37.398
You have embarrassed me and this office
for the last time.

1580
01:35:40.026 --> 01:35:41.319
I'm sorry. Colonel.

1581
01:35:43.154 --> 01:35:44.155
You deserved better.

1582
01:35:44.238 --> 01:35:45.323
Yes. I did.

1583
01:35:47.700 --> 01:35:52.080
And just so you know. we are releasing
Göring's wife and daughter.

1584
01:35:52.872 --> 01:35:54.624
You were right. We are better than that.

1585
01:35:59.837 --> 01:36:02.131
- Thank you. sir.
- Your train's at five o'clock.

1586
01:36:02.215 --> 01:36:03.508
[EXHALES]

1587
01:36:03.591 --> 01:36:06.219
Don't take this the wrong way.
but I never wanna see you again.

1588
01:36:09.764 --> 01:36:11.766
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [TRAIN HISSING]

1589
01:36:11.849 --> 01:36:13.851
[INDISTINCT GERMAN
ANNOUNCEMENT OVER RADIO]

1590
01:36:21.317 --> 01:36:22.902
DOUGLAS: Came to say goodbye?

1591
01:36:23.695 --> 01:36:26.656
Did you really mean it
when you said Jackson had no chance?

1592
01:36:26.739 --> 01:36:27.740
DOUGLAS: Sure.

1593
01:36:27.824 --> 01:36:29.951
It's all just a big show
for the cameras anyway.

1594
01:36:30.702 --> 01:36:32.161
So. it doesn't matter
what happens tomorrow.

1595
01:36:32.245 --> 01:36:34.622
If Göring beats Jackson. so be it.

1596
01:36:34.706 --> 01:36:35.999
Yeah. I don't believe that.

1597
01:36:38.710 --> 01:36:39.711
Neither do you.

1598
01:36:41.587 --> 01:36:43.840
You know more about him
than anybody on earth.

1599
01:36:45.133 --> 01:36:46.467
Yeah. that's right. I do.

1600
01:36:47.885 --> 01:36:51.639
I spent thousands of hours with him.
I run hundreds of tests.

1601
01:36:51.723 --> 01:36:53.433
You know what sets him apart from us?

1602
01:36:55.018 --> 01:36:56.102
Nothing.

1603
01:36:57.729 --> 01:36:58.730
I know.

1604
01:37:00.815 --> 01:37:01.816
You know?

1605
01:37:02.984 --> 01:37:04.402
'Cause I'm one of 'em.

1606
01:37:06.362 --> 01:37:07.447
What are you talking about?

1607
01:37:08.948 --> 01:37:10.450
I'm German. Doc.

1608
01:37:12.410 --> 01:37:13.661
I grew up in Munich.

1609
01:37:14.746 --> 01:37:17.415
You grew up in Detroit.
You said your mom spoke German.

1610
01:37:17.498 --> 01:37:19.709
She did. So did my father.

1611
01:37:21.753 --> 01:37:23.004
'Cause I was raised here.

1612
01:37:23.588 --> 01:37:25.006
You're an American soldier.

1613
01:37:28.051 --> 01:37:29.052
Why'd you leave?

1614
01:37:32.180 --> 01:37:33.264
Why do you think?

1615
01:37:39.187 --> 01:37:40.188
You're a Jew.

1616
01:37:48.946 --> 01:37:51.032
You know. with the blonde hair
and the blue eyes.

1617
01:37:51.115 --> 01:37:52.742
I never got hassled much.

1618
01:37:55.870 --> 01:37:59.624
My father was a patriot who fought
for Germany in the First World War.

1619
01:38:02.460 --> 01:38:03.920
We loved this country.

1620
01:38:06.005 --> 01:38:07.757
Eventually. he realized we had to get out.

1621
01:38:11.427 --> 01:38:12.428
How'd you do it?

1622
01:38:14.305 --> 01:38:16.224
The problem was getting travel visas.

1623
01:38:18.059 --> 01:38:19.685
Other countries wouldn't take us.

1624
01:38:21.020 --> 01:38:24.023
My dad had a cousin in New York
who helped.

1625
01:38:25.691 --> 01:38:27.860
We finally got our exit visas in 1940.

1626
01:38:30.071 --> 01:38:32.281
But we only had enough money
for one ticket out.

1627
01:38:35.701 --> 01:38:37.203
My little sister Margot...

1628
01:38:38.204 --> 01:38:39.413
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

1629
01:38:39.497 --> 01:38:41.082
She was only 11. so.

1630
01:38:41.999 --> 01:38:43.876
my parents didn't want her
traveling alone.

1631
01:38:45.795 --> 01:38:46.796
So they sent me.

1632
01:38:50.508 --> 01:38:52.510
Boy. I was seasick the whole way.
[CHUCKLES]

1633
01:38:56.722 --> 01:38:58.975
When I landed. I stayed with my cousin.

1634
01:39:01.769 --> 01:39:03.312
And the Nazis invaded Holland.

1635
01:39:07.984 --> 01:39:09.235
My family never showed up.

1636
01:39:13.447 --> 01:39:14.782
That's when I went to Detroit.

1637
01:39:17.243 --> 01:39:19.704
Got a job as an apprentice
in a tool factory.

1638
01:39:20.788 --> 01:39:23.249
Learned English listenin' to baseball
on the radio.

1639
01:39:25.334 --> 01:39:26.627
When Pearl Harbor happened...

1640
01:39:28.546 --> 01:39:31.591
I was the first one
at the recruitment office to enlist.

1641
01:39:34.343 --> 01:39:35.344
You know what they said?

1642
01:39:37.054 --> 01:39:40.266
They couldn't take me
'cause I wasn't an American citizen.

1643
01:39:42.768 --> 01:39:44.770
I'd have to wait to get drafted.

1644
01:39:47.815 --> 01:39:48.816
So I did.

1645
01:39:50.109 --> 01:39:51.777
I waited. and I waited.

1646
01:39:51.861 --> 01:39:55.281
and I checked the mailbox every day
for two years.

1647
01:39:58.451 --> 01:40:00.203
June 6. 1944...

1648
01:40:01.913 --> 01:40:04.749
landed at Omaha Beach on D-Day.

1649
01:40:10.004 --> 01:40:11.255
Four years earlier...

1650
01:40:13.966 --> 01:40:18.804
I left this country scared and alone
in the middle of the night.

1651
01:40:23.017 --> 01:40:25.478
But I came back with a goddamn army.

1652
01:40:29.523 --> 01:40:30.608
I found Margot.

1653
01:40:32.735 --> 01:40:35.112
She's in Switzerland.

1654
01:40:35.196 --> 01:40:37.740
She's 16 now. She's living with relatives.

1655
01:40:39.867 --> 01:40:40.868
She's good.

1656
01:40:42.286 --> 01:40:43.287
She made it.

1657
01:40:45.206 --> 01:40:46.207
And your folks?

1658
01:40:49.043 --> 01:40:53.631
Records show that my parents
arrived at Auschwitz.

1659
01:40:53.714 --> 01:40:55.633
August 12. 1942.

1660
01:40:58.886 --> 01:41:02.556
Camp was liberated January 27. 1945.

1661
01:41:03.516 --> 01:41:05.518
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1662
01:41:06.852 --> 01:41:07.853
No sign of 'em.

1663
01:41:10.648 --> 01:41:13.276
The Nazis had a name
for what they did to us.

1664
01:41:17.321 --> 01:41:18.656
"The Final Solution."

1665
01:41:23.202 --> 01:41:24.662
Like we were...

1666
01:41:27.081 --> 01:41:29.959
just some kinda nagging puzzle

1667
01:41:30.042 --> 01:41:32.545
that they finally figured out
how to solve.

1668
01:41:36.340 --> 01:41:37.758
So sorry. Howie.

1669
01:41:39.802 --> 01:41:41.721
I'm gonna tell Stretcher.

1670
01:41:45.057 --> 01:41:46.183
I'm gonna tell him.

1671
01:41:46.934 --> 01:41:49.687
Right before they put
that rope around his neck.

1672
01:41:49.770 --> 01:41:52.857
I'm gonna tell that piece of shit
that he was confiding in a Jew.

1673
01:41:57.778 --> 01:42:01.407
You say it doesn't matter
what happens tomorrow.

1674
01:42:06.954 --> 01:42:07.955
It matters.

1675
01:42:10.708 --> 01:42:11.834
More than you know.

1676
01:42:14.045 --> 01:42:15.046
Matters to me.

1677
01:42:17.506 --> 01:42:18.507
To my family.

1678
01:42:19.675 --> 01:42:21.052
[VOICE SHAKING] To all of Germany.

1679
01:42:21.552 --> 01:42:22.845
Göring has to fall.

1680
01:42:22.928 --> 01:42:24.930
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

1681
01:42:30.811 --> 01:42:32.980
If you think he's gonna beat Jackson...

1682
01:42:35.191 --> 01:42:38.652
Doc. please just do something about it.

1683
01:42:42.865 --> 01:42:43.866
I can't.

1684
01:42:47.244 --> 01:42:48.245
HOWIE: You can't?

1685
01:42:51.290 --> 01:42:52.375
I'm just a shrink.

1686
01:42:57.296 --> 01:42:58.297
[HOWIE SNIFFLES]

1687
01:43:09.892 --> 01:43:12.061
HOWIE: You wanna know
why it happened here?

1688
01:43:15.022 --> 01:43:16.357
'Cause people let it happen.

1689
01:43:18.234 --> 01:43:20.569
'Cause they didn't stand up
until it was too late.

1690
01:43:23.447 --> 01:43:25.074
Have a safe trip home. Doc.

1691
01:43:32.456 --> 01:43:33.457
[RAIN PATTERING]

1692
01:43:38.212 --> 01:43:39.839
Yes. sir. Of course.

1693
01:43:42.091 --> 01:43:45.219
No. I... I completely understand.

1694
01:43:47.721 --> 01:43:48.722
Thank you.

1695
01:43:50.850 --> 01:43:51.851
[SLAMS PHONE RECEIVER]

1696
01:43:51.934 --> 01:43:52.935
Son of a gun.

1697
01:43:55.187 --> 01:43:59.066
Truman just named Frederick Vinson
Chief Justice of the Supreme Court.

1698
01:43:59.150 --> 01:44:00.151
DAVID: Oh.

1699
01:44:01.944 --> 01:44:03.737
Ah. I didn't want the job anyway.

1700
01:44:03.821 --> 01:44:04.822
Who would?

1701
01:44:06.949 --> 01:44:07.950
Bottoms up.

1702
01:44:08.826 --> 01:44:09.910
- [GLASSES CLINKING]
- [DOOR OPENS]

1703
01:44:11.370 --> 01:44:12.705
You're walking into a trap.

1704
01:44:12.788 --> 01:44:15.583
Dr. Kelley. I was under the impression
you'd been relieved.

1705
01:44:15.666 --> 01:44:18.294
Putting Göring on the stand
gives him everything he wants.

1706
01:44:18.377 --> 01:44:20.379
It's why he surrendered
in the first place.

1707
01:44:20.463 --> 01:44:23.340
His last chance to redeem the Reich
on the world stage.

1708
01:44:23.424 --> 01:44:24.967
After what I read
in the paper this morning.

1709
01:44:25.050 --> 01:44:27.011
I don't believe
I care what you think anymore.

1710
01:44:27.094 --> 01:44:28.637
- You can't beat him!
- Guards!

1711
01:44:28.721 --> 01:44:30.306
- Not without help.
- [DOOR OPENS]

1712
01:44:31.599 --> 01:44:33.309
This is everything I have on him.

1713
01:44:33.392 --> 01:44:36.061
Private files. off-the-book conversations.

1714
01:44:36.145 --> 01:44:38.439
I know more about this man
than anyone else on the planet

1715
01:44:38.522 --> 01:44:39.815
and it's all in here.

1716
01:44:43.903 --> 01:44:44.904
Why do you have this?

1717
01:44:44.987 --> 01:44:45.988
[CHUCKLES]

1718
01:44:47.072 --> 01:44:48.282
I was gonna write a book.

1719
01:44:50.743 --> 01:44:52.369
Make something of myself. yeah.

1720
01:44:54.330 --> 01:44:55.331
JACKSON: Mmm.

1721
01:44:56.457 --> 01:44:57.458
It's okay.

1722
01:44:59.168 --> 01:45:01.545
So. you really think I can't beat him?

1723
01:45:01.629 --> 01:45:02.671
Honestly?

1724
01:45:05.257 --> 01:45:06.509
I don't know.

1725
01:45:07.676 --> 01:45:09.553
You know. I was gonna be Chief Justice.

1726
01:45:11.430 --> 01:45:14.683
Now I'll be lucky if there's a place
on the Court for me when I return.

1727
01:45:14.767 --> 01:45:17.937
As of six hours ago.
I was discharged from the army.

1728
01:45:18.729 --> 01:45:20.773
There's nothing left for us to do. sir.

1729
01:45:23.567 --> 01:45:25.486
Might as well go finish the war.

1730
01:45:28.197 --> 01:45:29.406
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1731
01:45:31.408 --> 01:45:32.409
JACKSON: Mmm-hmm.

1732
01:45:33.285 --> 01:45:34.912
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1733
01:45:35.496 --> 01:45:38.374
DOUGLAS: <i>The trick is to use
his vanity against him.</i>

1734
01:45:38.457 --> 01:45:39.959
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1735
01:45:40.042 --> 01:45:42.211
DOUGLAS: <i>He is the</i> Reichsmarschall.

1736
01:45:42.294 --> 01:45:44.797
<i>And the</i> Reichsmarschall <i>is never wrong.</i>

1737
01:45:45.464 --> 01:45:46.465
<i>He can't be.</i>

1738
01:45:47.174 --> 01:45:51.887
<i>Every decision that's led him
to this place has to be the right one.</i>

1739
01:45:51.971 --> 01:45:54.932
<i>So. as much as he won't wanna
talk about the camps</i>

1740
01:45:55.015 --> 01:45:57.434
<i>and the SS and the Final Solution.</i>

1741
01:45:58.435 --> 01:45:59.979
<i>you can make him own them.</i>

1742
01:46:01.146 --> 01:46:02.398
ELSIE: <i>Kelley's right.</i>

1743
01:46:02.481 --> 01:46:05.276
<i>Get him to admit to signing those orders.</i>

1744
01:46:05.943 --> 01:46:07.152
and you'll have him.

1745
01:46:08.988 --> 01:46:09.989
I'll have him.

1746
01:46:10.072 --> 01:46:11.031
[CHUCKLES]

1747
01:46:13.659 --> 01:46:14.660
This is your day.

1748
01:46:15.995 --> 01:46:16.996
You're ready.

1749
01:46:20.958 --> 01:46:22.960
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

1750
01:46:38.684 --> 01:46:40.686
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1751
01:46:40.686 --> 01:47:10.686
<b>Subtitle 
 www.movieddl.me</b>

1752
01:47:20.100 --> 01:47:21.727
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

1753
01:47:28.567 --> 01:47:30.903
Sergeant. what is Doug Kelley
still doing here?

1754
01:47:33.238 --> 01:47:34.239
HOWIE: No idea. sir.

1755
01:47:37.534 --> 01:47:38.619
BAILIFF: All rise!

1756
01:47:53.050 --> 01:47:55.761
Justice Jackson. are you ready?

1757
01:48:01.517 --> 01:48:02.726
[SLURPING]

1758
01:48:03.769 --> 01:48:04.770
[EXHALES]

1759
01:48:13.987 --> 01:48:17.157
The prosecution now calls
Hermann Göring to the stand.

1760
01:48:17.241 --> 01:48:19.243
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1761
01:49:01.285 --> 01:49:02.286
[CAMERA WHIRRING]

1762
01:49:06.373 --> 01:49:10.669
For the record. is there any doubt
in your mind that Adolf Hitler is dead?

1763
01:49:14.673 --> 01:49:16.091
I have no doubt.

1764
01:49:17.593 --> 01:49:21.346
So. you are aware that this makes you
the only living man

1765
01:49:21.430 --> 01:49:25.476
who can expound to us the true purposes
of the Nazi Party

1766
01:49:25.559 --> 01:49:27.478
and the inner workings of its leadership?

1767
01:49:28.854 --> 01:49:30.814
I am perfectly aware of this. yeah.

1768
01:49:30.898 --> 01:49:31.857
JACKSON: Mmm-hmm.

1769
01:49:32.775 --> 01:49:37.738
Your party. from the very beginning.
intended to overthrow the Weimar Republic?

1770
01:49:40.157 --> 01:49:41.909
That was our firm intention.

1771
01:49:41.992 --> 01:49:43.076
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

1772
01:49:43.160 --> 01:49:44.328
What the hell?

1773
01:49:44.411 --> 01:49:45.746
And upon coming to power.

1774
01:49:45.829 --> 01:49:48.957
you immediately abolished
parliamentary government in Germany?

1775
01:49:49.041 --> 01:49:51.335
We found it to be no longer necessary.

1776
01:49:52.336 --> 01:49:55.714
Is that because you believed people
are not capable of self-government?

1777
01:49:58.467 --> 01:50:03.555
We were elected by the people
and given a mandate for change.

1778
01:50:04.139 --> 01:50:06.225
[OVER SPEAKERS] <i>The system
that had previously existed</i>

1779
01:50:06.308 --> 01:50:09.019
<i>had brought Germany to the verge of ruin.</i>

1780
01:50:09.102 --> 01:50:11.480
<i>Your own President Roosevelt said.</i>

1781
01:50:11.563 --> 01:50:16.068
"There are certain peoples in Europe
who have forsaken democracy

1782
01:50:16.151 --> 01:50:18.403
"not because they did not wish for it.

1783
01:50:19.279 --> 01:50:23.033
"but because democracy had brought forth
men who were too weak."

1784
01:50:24.785 --> 01:50:26.411
[SOFTLY] Get to war crimes.

1785
01:50:26.912 --> 01:50:28.330
After you came to power.

1786
01:50:28.413 --> 01:50:33.210
you regarded it necessary to suppress
all opposition parties. correct?

1787
01:50:33.293 --> 01:50:37.464
We found it necessary
to no longer permit opposition. yeah.

1788
01:50:37.923 --> 01:50:40.342
And you also considered it
immediately necessary

1789
01:50:40.425 --> 01:50:42.261
to establish concentration camps?

1790
01:50:43.303 --> 01:50:47.349
The camps were set up as a measure
against the Communists

1791
01:50:48.016 --> 01:50:49.351
and their violence.

1792
01:50:49.434 --> 01:50:52.396
So. it was necessary
to erect a camp for them.

1793
01:50:52.479 --> 01:50:54.648
One. two. or three camps.
something like this.

1794
01:50:55.482 --> 01:50:58.402
You also had to have certain groups

1795
01:50:58.485 --> 01:51:01.655
to carry out orders
and fight for you if necessary. right?

1796
01:51:02.573 --> 01:51:03.699
Certain groups?

1797
01:51:03.782 --> 01:51:06.076
Well. for example.
if you wanted certain people killed.

1798
01:51:06.952 --> 01:51:09.413
you had to have some organization
that would kill them.

1799
01:51:10.706 --> 01:51:13.000
Yeah. Germany had this level
of political police

1800
01:51:13.083 --> 01:51:14.543
as you would find in any other country.

1801
01:51:14.626 --> 01:51:16.128
And the SA and the SS

1802
01:51:16.211 --> 01:51:19.089
were the organizations
that carried out these orders

1803
01:51:19.172 --> 01:51:22.134
and dealt with people on a physical level.
were they not?

1804
01:51:22.217 --> 01:51:25.470
The SA never received orders
to kill anybody.

1805
01:51:25.554 --> 01:51:27.472
Neither did the SS. Not in my time.

1806
01:51:27.556 --> 01:51:30.142
Beyond a certain point.
I had no influence on it.

1807
01:51:31.101 --> 01:51:33.520
Well. the SS carried out arrests.

1808
01:51:34.771 --> 01:51:37.691
They handled the transportation of people
to the concentration camps.

1809
01:51:37.774 --> 01:51:39.818
Can you not recall a time

1810
01:51:39.902 --> 01:51:41.653
when the SS began to perform the function

1811
01:51:41.737 --> 01:51:44.281
of acting as the executor
of the Nazi Party?

1812
01:51:44.364 --> 01:51:47.409
It would be very difficult for me
to explain to an outsider

1813
01:51:47.492 --> 01:51:50.871
where the SS or where the <i>Gestapo</i>
may or may not be active.

1814
01:51:52.247 --> 01:51:53.248
Try.

1815
01:51:54.041 --> 01:51:58.837
Well. perhaps. as the police came more
and more into the hands of Himmler.

1816
01:51:59.379 --> 01:52:00.881
expectations may have changed.

1817
01:52:00.964 --> 01:52:04.051
And. of course. it is well-known
that some SS units

1818
01:52:04.134 --> 01:52:08.764
were guarding the camps. and later.
performed some police functions.

1819
01:52:09.890 --> 01:52:14.102
And carried out other functions
in the camps?

1820
01:52:14.895 --> 01:52:16.730
To what functions do you refer?

1821
01:52:18.398 --> 01:52:22.986
They carried out all of the functions
of the camps. didn't they?

1822
01:52:23.570 --> 01:52:24.571
[HERMANN SIGHS]

1823
01:52:28.742 --> 01:52:31.787
If an SS unit was guarding a camp

1824
01:52:33.080 --> 01:52:36.416
and an SS leader was the camp commandant.

1825
01:52:37.751 --> 01:52:40.128
then it is rational to assume

1826
01:52:41.129 --> 01:52:45.759
that they would have carried out
all of the functions of the camp.

1827
01:52:46.969 --> 01:52:47.970
[SOFTLY] Bury him.

1828
01:52:48.053 --> 01:52:51.348
You have said that you wanted
a strong German State

1829
01:52:51.431 --> 01:52:54.267
to overcome the conditions of Versailles.
is that correct?

1830
01:52:54.351 --> 01:52:58.021
We wanted a strong German State.
regardless of Versailles.

1831
01:52:58.105 --> 01:53:00.857
The first country to be absorbed
by Germany was Austria

1832
01:53:00.941 --> 01:53:04.486
but it had not been part of Germany
before the First World War

1833
01:53:04.569 --> 01:53:06.321
and it had not been taken from Germany

1834
01:53:06.405 --> 01:53:07.990
by the Treaty of Versailles.
is that correct?

1835
01:53:08.073 --> 01:53:10.075
That is not entirely correct. no.

1836
01:53:10.158 --> 01:53:13.203
JACKSON: The second territory taken
by Germany was Bohemia.

1837
01:53:13.286 --> 01:53:15.247
[OVER SPEAKERS]
<i>then Moravia. and then Slovakia.</i>

1838
01:53:15.330 --> 01:53:16.498
[SLAMS TABLE]

1839
01:53:16.581 --> 01:53:20.335
These were not taken from Germany
by the Treaty of Versailles

1840
01:53:20.419 --> 01:53:24.381
nor had they been part of Germany
before the First World War. had they?

1841
01:53:24.464 --> 01:53:26.717
These parts of Czech territory

1842
01:53:26.800 --> 01:53:32.222
were not parts of the smaller German Reich
at the time of the Treaty of Versailles.

1843
01:53:32.305 --> 01:53:33.598
However. formerly.

1844
01:53:34.266 --> 01:53:36.977
they were united to the German Reich...

1845
01:53:38.603 --> 01:53:40.147
for hundreds of years.

1846
01:53:40.230 --> 01:53:42.190
You still have not answered my question.

1847
01:53:42.274 --> 01:53:43.608
HERMANN: I have answered your question.

1848
01:53:43.692 --> 01:53:47.320
If the facts do not suit you.
there's very little I can do.

1849
01:53:47.404 --> 01:53:49.031
Can you not answer "yes" or "no"?

1850
01:53:49.114 --> 01:53:53.368
Time may not mean quite as much to you
as it does to the rest of us.

1851
01:53:53.452 --> 01:53:56.663
Mr. Justice. the Tribunal thinks
the witness ought to be allowed

1852
01:53:56.747 --> 01:54:00.375
to make what explanations he thinks right.

1853
01:54:00.959 --> 01:54:04.463
I trust that the Court is not unaware
that outside of this courtroom

1854
01:54:04.546 --> 01:54:07.758
is a great social question
regarding the revival of Nazism.

1855
01:54:07.841 --> 01:54:09.301
[OVER SPEAKERS]
<i>and that one of the purposes</i>

1856
01:54:09.384 --> 01:54:10.677
<i>of defendant Göring</i>

1857
01:54:10.761 --> 01:54:13.055
is to encourage and perpetuate it

1858
01:54:13.138 --> 01:54:16.141
by propaganda from this trial
now in process.

1859
01:54:16.224 --> 01:54:18.435
- JUDGE FRANCIS: Mr. Justice...
- This witness has adopted

1860
01:54:18.518 --> 01:54:21.063
in the witness box and the prisoner's dock

1861
01:54:21.146 --> 01:54:24.816
an arrogant and contemptuous attitude
towards this Tribunal

1862
01:54:24.900 --> 01:54:28.570
which is giving him
the opportunity of a trial.

1863
01:54:28.653 --> 01:54:30.030
which he never gave a living soul!

1864
01:54:30.113 --> 01:54:32.949
The ruling stands. Mr. Justice.

1865
01:54:38.789 --> 01:54:42.084
[SIGHS] I must. of course.
bow to the ruling of the Tribunal.

1866
01:54:43.460 --> 01:54:48.256
and would simply request that the witness
find a way to keep his answers succinct.

1867
01:54:52.302 --> 01:54:54.846
Could you please repeat the question?

1868
01:54:54.930 --> 01:54:56.431
[ALL LAUGHING]

1869
01:54:56.515 --> 01:54:59.893
They were not taken from you

1870
01:55:00.560 --> 01:55:03.605
- by the Treaty of Versailles. were they?
- Of course.

1871
01:55:03.688 --> 01:55:06.441
Austria was taken
by the Versailles Treaty.

1872
01:55:06.525 --> 01:55:07.859
and was too Sudetenland.

1873
01:55:09.986 --> 01:55:13.824
For both these territories
would have been German territories

1874
01:55:13.907 --> 01:55:15.826
through the simple right of the people

1875
01:55:15.909 --> 01:55:17.869
- to self-determination.
- [JACKSON SCOFFS]

1876
01:55:19.162 --> 01:55:20.539
Now. I find that interesting

1877
01:55:21.498 --> 01:55:24.501
considering you just testified
that people's self-determination

1878
01:55:24.584 --> 01:55:26.628
was the first thing you took away.

1879
01:55:26.711 --> 01:55:27.879
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

1880
01:55:29.005 --> 01:55:30.715
JACKSON: From the very beginning.

1881
01:55:30.799 --> 01:55:35.762
you regarded the elimination of Jews
from the economic life of Germany

1882
01:55:35.846 --> 01:55:40.767
as one phase of the Four-Year Plan
under your jurisdiction. is that correct?

1883
01:55:40.851 --> 01:55:42.936
- Partially correct.
- JACKSON: "Partially."

1884
01:55:43.728 --> 01:55:44.729
I see.

1885
01:55:45.480 --> 01:55:49.192
I would like to review with you briefly.

1886
01:55:50.068 --> 01:55:53.780
public acts taken by you
in reference to the Jewish question.

1887
01:55:54.406 --> 01:55:57.367
First. did you proclaim
the Nuremberg Laws?

1888
01:56:00.036 --> 01:56:01.580
[SMACKS LIPS] Yeah. I did.

1889
01:56:01.663 --> 01:56:04.416
As President of the <i>Reichstag.</i>
that was my job.

1890
01:56:05.208 --> 01:56:06.334
JACKSON: What date was that?

1891
01:56:07.669 --> 01:56:09.880
15th of September. 1935.

1892
01:56:09.963 --> 01:56:13.425
Then on the first day of December 1936.

1893
01:56:13.508 --> 01:56:16.428
you passed an act
making it a death penalty for Germans

1894
01:56:16.511 --> 01:56:18.221
to transfer property abroad?

1895
01:56:19.055 --> 01:56:20.140
That is correct.

1896
01:56:20.223 --> 01:56:23.310
That was the "Decree Governing Restriction
on Foreign Currency."

1897
01:56:23.393 --> 01:56:26.271
Then. on April 22. 1938.
you published penalties

1898
01:56:26.354 --> 01:56:30.108
for concealing the character
of a Jewish enterprise within the Reich.

1899
01:56:30.192 --> 01:56:31.735
"Concealing." yeah.

1900
01:56:31.818 --> 01:56:34.529
Then. on April 26. 1938.
you signed a decree

1901
01:56:34.613 --> 01:56:38.783
ordering the registration of all Jewish
property inside and outside of Germany.

1902
01:56:40.118 --> 01:56:43.663
- If it is signed by me...
- Then a decree on November 12. 1938.

1903
01:56:43.747 --> 01:56:48.501
imposing a fine of one billion Reichsmarks
for atonement on all Jews.

1904
01:56:48.585 --> 01:56:50.462
- Yeah. but that is...
- JACKSON: And that all damages

1905
01:56:50.545 --> 01:56:53.715
caused to Jewish property
by the riots of 1938

1906
01:56:53.798 --> 01:56:57.552
must be repaired by Jews immediately
at their own expense.

1907
01:56:57.636 --> 01:56:59.804
and their insurance claims
forfeited to the Reich.

1908
01:56:59.888 --> 01:57:01.514
There are many details here.

1909
01:57:01.598 --> 01:57:03.600
- The insurance...
- JACKSON: And a decree

1910
01:57:03.683 --> 01:57:05.518
on the 17th of September. 1940.

1911
01:57:05.602 --> 01:57:08.313
ordering the sequestration
of all Jewish property in Poland.

1912
01:57:08.396 --> 01:57:12.484
Yeah. In that part of Poland.
it was a former German province

1913
01:57:12.567 --> 01:57:15.820
- And on July 31. 1941 ...
- ...and would return to Germany.

1914
01:57:15.904 --> 01:57:18.448
...a decree asking Himmler and Heydrich

1915
01:57:19.366 --> 01:57:22.994
to make plans for the Final Solution
of the Jewish question.

1916
01:57:30.335 --> 01:57:31.336
That is not correct.

1917
01:57:32.087 --> 01:57:33.546
I know that decree very well.

1918
01:57:34.881 --> 01:57:37.842
I ask to have you shown Document 710.

1919
01:57:38.635 --> 01:57:40.428
exhibit number USA-509.

1920
01:57:43.265 --> 01:57:44.933
I think it should be read into the record

1921
01:57:45.016 --> 01:57:47.644
so we may have no argument
about its translation.

1922
01:57:47.727 --> 01:57:48.770
<i>Danke schön.</i>

1923
01:57:54.067 --> 01:57:56.903
[IN ENGLISH] That document
is signed by you. is it not?

1924
01:57:58.905 --> 01:57:59.948
That is correct.

1925
01:58:00.699 --> 01:58:02.701
Please correct me if I am wrong.

1926
01:58:05.412 --> 01:58:09.249
"Supplementing the task
that was assigned to you on 1-24-1939

1927
01:58:10.166 --> 01:58:11.584
"which dealt with arriving at...

1928
01:58:12.669 --> 01:58:16.047
"through furtherance of emigration
and evacuation

1929
01:58:16.131 --> 01:58:20.010
"a solution of the Jewish problem.
as advantageous as possible.

1930
01:58:20.093 --> 01:58:23.972
"I hereby charge you with making
all necessary preparations

1931
01:58:24.055 --> 01:58:25.473
"in regards to organizational

1932
01:58:25.557 --> 01:58:28.226
"and financial matters
for bringing about...

1933
01:58:29.769 --> 01:58:33.106
"a final solution of the Jewish question."

1934
01:58:34.232 --> 01:58:35.275
He's got him.

1935
01:58:35.358 --> 01:58:36.359
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

1936
01:58:38.695 --> 01:58:40.030
JACKSON: Am I correct so far?

1937
01:58:42.198 --> 01:58:44.868
No. Your translation is not correct.

1938
01:58:47.829 --> 01:58:50.165
Then. please. give us your translation.

1939
01:58:51.166 --> 01:58:52.167
[CHAIR CREAKING]

1940
01:58:55.170 --> 01:58:59.549
"Supplementing the task
which was entrusted to you

1941
01:59:00.592 --> 01:59:03.803
"in the decree dated January 24. 1939.

1942
01:59:03.887 --> 01:59:07.390
"to solve the Jewish question
by emigration and evacuation

1943
01:59:07.474 --> 01:59:10.185
"in the most favorable way possible.

1944
01:59:12.395 --> 01:59:15.440
"Given present conditions.
I herewith commission you

1945
01:59:15.523 --> 01:59:18.318
"to carry out all necessary preparations

1946
01:59:18.401 --> 01:59:22.822
"with regard to organizational.
substantive. and financial viewpoints."

1947
01:59:24.074 --> 01:59:25.325
Now. here is...

1948
01:59:26.576 --> 01:59:27.952
the sentence.

1949
01:59:28.036 --> 01:59:31.498
"For a complete solution."

1950
01:59:31.581 --> 01:59:32.707
not "a final solution."

1951
01:59:33.625 --> 01:59:36.836
"For a total solution
of the Jewish question."

1952
01:59:39.631 --> 01:59:42.717
[SMACKS LIPS]
"A complete and total solution"?

1953
01:59:42.801 --> 01:59:45.011
HERMANN: Complete and total. yeah.

1954
01:59:45.095 --> 01:59:50.141
A complete and total solution
you wanted the Chief of the SS to enact?

1955
01:59:51.184 --> 01:59:54.354
Yeah. but I would like to make
an explanation.

1956
01:59:54.896 --> 01:59:55.980
Oh. please do.

1957
01:59:58.858 --> 02:00:02.862
I sent this letter
to Himmler and to Heydrich

1958
02:00:03.988 --> 02:00:06.908
because it was some 18 months now

1959
02:00:06.991 --> 02:00:10.412
since the declaration
of 24th of January. 1939.

1960
02:00:10.495 --> 02:00:12.705
And Heydrich had achieved very little.

1961
02:00:13.581 --> 02:00:16.042
so. I charged him to accelerate the task

1962
02:00:16.126 --> 02:00:18.336
of dealing with the emigration
of the Jews.

1963
02:00:21.381 --> 02:00:25.051
"Emigration"? You contend
this letter was about emigration?

1964
02:00:26.511 --> 02:00:28.763
It says so in the first line.

1965
02:00:38.273 --> 02:00:40.150
That's just the first sentence.

1966
02:00:40.233 --> 02:00:41.693
The letter goes on to state...

1967
02:00:41.776 --> 02:00:42.986
My desire...

1968
02:00:44.028 --> 02:00:46.489
for a complete solution
to the Jewish problem.

1969
02:00:47.240 --> 02:00:50.160
and an end to their financial influence

1970
02:00:50.243 --> 02:00:53.204
by their emigration and evacuation
from Germany.

1971
02:00:55.707 --> 02:00:59.127
It is in this document
that you presented to me.

1972
02:00:59.210 --> 02:01:00.503
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

1973
02:01:10.096 --> 02:01:12.682
JUDGE FRANCIS: Do you have
any more questions for the witness.

1974
02:01:12.765 --> 02:01:13.808
Justice Jackson?

1975
02:01:18.271 --> 02:01:19.439
[SIGHS]

1976
02:01:22.108 --> 02:01:25.236
Mr. Justice. is the witness excused?

1977
02:01:32.535 --> 02:01:33.995
DAVID: I have a question.

1978
02:01:39.876 --> 02:01:42.295
Uh. the Tribunal was under the impression

1979
02:01:42.378 --> 02:01:46.382
the American prosecutor would be examining
this witness today.

1980
02:01:47.550 --> 02:01:50.094
JACKSON: Uh. the United States
is always happy to hear

1981
02:01:50.178 --> 02:01:52.931
from our distinguished colleague
from Great Britain.

1982
02:02:01.314 --> 02:02:03.191
DAVID: Just a few simple queries.
Your Honors.

1983
02:02:03.274 --> 02:02:04.692
Won't take more than a moment.

1984
02:02:05.944 --> 02:02:09.656
You've implied to this Court
that you lost some influence

1985
02:02:09.739 --> 02:02:12.200
with Adolf Hitler in 1942.
is that correct?

1986
02:02:13.159 --> 02:02:15.870
I believe this to be the case. yeah.

1987
02:02:15.954 --> 02:02:19.791
But you were still
<i>Reichsmarschall</i> of Germany in 1942.

1988
02:02:20.416 --> 02:02:22.460
Hitler's successor. yes?

1989
02:02:24.754 --> 02:02:26.923
Yeah. I was the <i>Reichsmarschall.</i>

1990
02:02:28.132 --> 02:02:30.843
DAVID: And you're telling me
that you were totally unaware

1991
02:02:30.927 --> 02:02:34.556
three million Jews were murdered in 1942?

1992
02:02:39.644 --> 02:02:41.145
I was unaware of this.

1993
02:02:41.229 --> 02:02:45.608
In 1943. at least 800.000 Jews

1994
02:02:45.692 --> 02:02:47.026
were executed in the camps.

1995
02:02:47.110 --> 02:02:50.905
You were still <i>Reichsmarschall</i> in 1943.
is that correct?

1996
02:02:52.574 --> 02:02:53.908
- That is correct.
- DAVID: Hmm.

1997
02:02:53.992 --> 02:02:59.581
In 1944. an additional 800.000 Jews
died in the camps.

1998
02:02:59.664 --> 02:03:03.001
You were still <i>Reichsmarschall</i> in 1944.
is that correct?

1999
02:03:04.419 --> 02:03:05.461
That is correct.

2000
02:03:05.545 --> 02:03:10.216
In 1945. 250.000.

2001
02:03:10.300 --> 02:03:13.595
an estimated six million Jews in total.

2002
02:03:13.678 --> 02:03:16.514
as well as Soviet and Polish citizens.

2003
02:03:16.598 --> 02:03:19.892
Romani people. artists. scientists.

2004
02:03:19.976 --> 02:03:22.895
writers. journalists.
photographers. filmmakers.

2005
02:03:22.979 --> 02:03:25.648
people killed. not in combat.

2006
02:03:25.732 --> 02:03:27.650
not in enemy fire.

2007
02:03:27.734 --> 02:03:30.486
but exterminated by the state of Germany.

2008
02:03:30.570 --> 02:03:34.657
the State which you
were the <i>Reichsmarschall</i> of.

2009
02:03:34.741 --> 02:03:37.160
the pre-eminent political post
of your country.

2010
02:03:38.286 --> 02:03:42.540
and you contend that you had no knowledge.

2011
02:03:48.087 --> 02:03:49.422
At least give me this.

2012
02:03:50.840 --> 02:03:52.508
Knowing what we know now.

2013
02:03:53.593 --> 02:03:58.139
knowing what happened to six million Jews.
I have to ask...

2014
02:04:02.352 --> 02:04:06.522
Would you still follow
the <i>Führer.</i> Adolf Hitler?

2015
02:04:16.032 --> 02:04:17.033
Yeah...

2016
02:04:18.951 --> 02:04:19.952
I would.

2017
02:04:20.036 --> 02:04:21.037
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

2018
02:04:23.956 --> 02:04:25.583
Order! Order!

2019
02:04:29.379 --> 02:04:30.380
<i>Heil Hitler.</i>

2020
02:04:30.463 --> 02:04:32.090
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

2021
02:04:33.257 --> 02:04:34.425
No further questions.

2022
02:04:42.183 --> 02:04:44.435
JUDGE FRANCIS: I think
this as good a place as any

2023
02:04:44.519 --> 02:04:47.063
to adjourn for the day.

2024
02:04:47.146 --> 02:04:48.439
[GAVEL BANGING]

2025
02:04:49.440 --> 02:04:50.900
[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC PLAYING]

2026
02:04:53.444 --> 02:04:54.737
Fought brilliant.

2027
02:04:54.821 --> 02:04:55.822
Absolutely brilliant.

2028
02:04:58.032 --> 02:04:59.534
- I survived.
- You did it.

2029
02:05:25.351 --> 02:05:26.519
JACKSON: You were right.

2030
02:05:28.688 --> 02:05:29.897
I couldn't beat him.

2031
02:05:30.732 --> 02:05:31.941
Not without help.

2032
02:05:32.942 --> 02:05:34.902
"Göring cannot stand against the <i>Führer."</i>

2033
02:05:34.986 --> 02:05:36.904
- Invaluable information. Doctor.
- DOUGLAS: Hmm.

2034
02:05:40.283 --> 02:05:41.284
So. what now?

2035
02:05:43.202 --> 02:05:45.371
As Göring falls. so do they all.

2036
02:05:46.706 --> 02:05:47.707
We'll be okay.

2037
02:05:48.624 --> 02:05:49.625
Here.

2038
02:05:52.128 --> 02:05:53.129
[DOUGLAS CHUCKLES]

2039
02:05:53.880 --> 02:05:55.006
You off?

2040
02:05:56.466 --> 02:05:58.301
Uh. one more thing I have to do.

2041
02:06:04.432 --> 02:06:05.433
[KEYS JANGLING]

2042
02:06:06.434 --> 02:06:08.060
[CELL DOOR UNLOCKING]

2043
02:06:18.529 --> 02:06:19.739
- HERMANN: <i>Doktor.</i>
- [CELL DOOR LOCKS]

2044
02:06:22.867 --> 02:06:24.535
You helped them. didn't you?

2045
02:06:25.787 --> 02:06:26.788
I did.

2046
02:06:29.123 --> 02:06:30.124
I'm leaving.

2047
02:06:31.918 --> 02:06:32.919
HERMANN: Leaving?

2048
02:06:35.129 --> 02:06:36.130
Going home.

2049
02:06:38.216 --> 02:06:39.717
I've come to say goodbye.

2050
02:06:43.971 --> 02:06:45.515
What do we do now. Doctor?

2051
02:06:47.600 --> 02:06:48.768
Do we shake hands?

2052
02:06:53.689 --> 02:06:55.858
I know we were friends. Douglas...

2053
02:06:58.444 --> 02:06:59.445
for a while.

2054
02:07:09.038 --> 02:07:10.122
Goodbye. Hermann.

2055
02:07:16.963 --> 02:07:18.214
HERMANN: Years from now...

2056
02:07:20.258 --> 02:07:22.385
I wonder what you will say about us.

2057
02:07:23.678 --> 02:07:25.847
Will you even acknowledge we were human?

2058
02:07:45.491 --> 02:07:49.704
JUDGE LAWRENCE: The judgement
of the International Military Tribunal

2059
02:07:49.787 --> 02:07:50.788
will now be read.

2060
02:07:52.081 --> 02:07:55.334
Each defendant will be addressed in turn.

2061
02:07:55.418 --> 02:07:57.044
[WOMEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

2062
02:07:58.462 --> 02:08:00.006
JUDGE LAWRENCE: Hermann Göring.

2063
02:08:01.340 --> 02:08:04.510
the evidence shows that. after Hitler.

2064
02:08:04.594 --> 02:08:08.598
you were the most prominent man
in the Nazi regime.

2065
02:08:08.681 --> 02:08:09.891
[TRAIN HISSING]

2066
02:08:11.017 --> 02:08:14.186
<i>Your guilt is unique in its enormity.</i>

2067
02:08:15.688 --> 02:08:18.649
<i>Your record discloses no excuses.</i>

2068
02:08:20.776 --> 02:08:24.447
The International Military Tribunal
sentences you

2069
02:08:25.489 --> 02:08:27.074
to death by hanging.

2070
02:08:27.700 --> 02:08:29.702
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

2071
02:08:38.920 --> 02:08:40.504
Rudolf Hess.

2072
02:08:41.547 --> 02:08:44.342
You are indicted on all four counts.

2073
02:08:46.302 --> 02:08:49.847
The executions are scheduled
for midnight tonight.

2074
02:08:50.973 --> 02:08:52.850
In order to maintain discipline.

2075
02:08:53.559 --> 02:08:58.481
the prisoners will not be informed
until 11 :45 p.m.

2076
02:08:58.564 --> 02:09:02.360
when they will be awakened in their cells
and offered last rites.

2077
02:09:03.444 --> 02:09:08.199
At 8:00 p.m.. eight hand-picked
journalists will arrive at the prison.

2078
02:09:08.282 --> 02:09:12.078
<i>Two French. two British.
two American. two Russian.</i>

2079
02:09:13.496 --> 02:09:15.539
<i>Lights out is at 9:</i><i>30.</i>

2080
02:09:15.623 --> 02:09:18.668
<i>which is when the doctor
will do his normal final rounds.</i>

2081
02:09:18.751 --> 02:09:23.297
<i>Any prisoner requesting a sleep aid
will be given a placebo with baking soda.</i>

2082
02:09:23.381 --> 02:09:25.383
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

2083
02:09:26.300 --> 02:09:27.843
ANDRUS: [IN ENGLISH] <i>At ten o'clock.</i>

2084
02:09:27.927 --> 02:09:30.554
<i>we will bring the press
down to the gallows</i>

2085
02:09:30.638 --> 02:09:34.183
<i>where I will brief them
on the final preparations for tonight.</i>

2086
02:09:34.266 --> 02:09:36.268
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

2087
02:09:46.821 --> 02:09:47.822
[DOCTOR SPEAKING GERMAN]

2088
02:09:48.864 --> 02:09:49.865
<i>Nein.</i>

2089
02:09:51.033 --> 02:09:52.034
[DOCTOR SPEAKING GERMAN]

2090
02:10:00.668 --> 02:10:02.670
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

2091
02:10:04.588 --> 02:10:06.215
[HERMANN SIGHS DEEPLY]

2092
02:10:22.481 --> 02:10:23.899
[IN ENGLISH] Abracadabra.

2093
02:10:27.403 --> 02:10:28.237
[CAPSULE CRUNCHES]

2094
02:10:28.320 --> 02:10:31.032
The prisoners will be brought in
one-by-one.

2095
02:10:31.824 --> 02:10:35.036
and given the opportunity
to speak their last words.

2096
02:10:35.119 --> 02:10:36.287
- They will then...
- [ALARM BLARING]

2097
02:10:36.370 --> 02:10:38.372
- [INDISTINCT SHOUTING]
- [PEOPLE MURMURING]

2098
02:10:40.583 --> 02:10:41.584
Excuse me.

2099
02:10:46.464 --> 02:10:47.715
- Who is it?
- Göring. sir.

2100
02:10:47.798 --> 02:10:48.799
Shit.

2101
02:10:48.883 --> 02:10:50.092
[ALARM CONTINUES BLARING]

2102
02:10:55.723 --> 02:10:58.350
No. no. No. No!

2103
02:10:58.434 --> 02:11:00.436
No. you son of a bitch!
You don't get to do this.

2104
02:11:00.519 --> 02:11:02.521
SOLDIER: He's dead. sir. Cyanide.

2105
02:11:02.605 --> 02:11:03.689
ANDRUS: God damn it!

2106
02:11:07.193 --> 02:11:08.986
[SOFTLY] Oh. you son of a bitch.

2107
02:11:13.741 --> 02:11:16.619
I'm sorry. sir.
but we have a decision to make.

2108
02:11:17.453 --> 02:11:20.539
We can either scrub the executions
for tonight or proceed.

2109
02:11:21.123 --> 02:11:22.708
Let's just get on with it.

2110
02:11:22.792 --> 02:11:26.128
Sir. Uh. Stretcher's refusing
to put his clothes on.

2111
02:11:29.465 --> 02:11:31.467
[SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

2112
02:11:33.761 --> 02:11:35.638
- [IN ENGLISH] Let him go. Let him go!
- SOLDIER: But. sir...

2113
02:11:35.721 --> 02:11:36.722
[GROANS]

2114
02:11:38.599 --> 02:11:39.642
[CRYING]

2115
02:11:47.149 --> 02:11:48.776
[JULIUS SOBBING]

2116
02:11:50.653 --> 02:11:51.654
Julius.

2117
02:11:54.031 --> 02:11:55.032
Julius.

2118
02:11:57.159 --> 02:11:58.160
[JULIUS SOBBING]

2119
02:12:01.664 --> 02:12:02.665
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

2120
02:12:05.126 --> 02:12:06.127
[SNIFFLES]

2121
02:12:07.211 --> 02:12:08.212
[IN ENGLISH] You...

2122
02:12:10.756 --> 02:12:12.341
You have been a friend.

2123
02:12:14.260 --> 02:12:15.261
[JULIUS CRYING]

2124
02:12:24.019 --> 02:12:25.396
[CLEARS THROAT] Come on.

2125
02:12:27.398 --> 02:12:28.649
Let's do it together.

2126
02:12:29.900 --> 02:12:31.485
- [JULIUS WHIMPERING]
- Come on.

2127
02:12:33.779 --> 02:12:34.864
Give me his shirt.

2128
02:12:34.947 --> 02:12:36.073
[CRYING]

2129
02:12:48.169 --> 02:12:50.171
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

2130
02:13:08.439 --> 02:13:10.065
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

2131
02:13:32.588 --> 02:13:33.881
COLONEL FRANKS: Ask him his name.

2132
02:13:34.548 --> 02:13:37.051
JULIUS: You know my name.

2133
02:13:37.134 --> 02:13:38.761
Any last words?

2134
02:13:39.428 --> 02:13:42.431
Purim Feast. 1946!

2135
02:13:43.682 --> 02:13:44.892
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

2136
02:13:51.857 --> 02:13:52.858
[JULIUS CRYING]

2137
02:13:57.154 --> 02:13:59.782
[SOBBING. SPEAKING GERMAN]

2138
02:14:14.797 --> 02:14:16.799
- [LEVER CLANKS]
- [GALLOW THUDS]

2139
02:14:16.882 --> 02:14:18.050
[ROPE CREAKING]

2140
02:14:20.094 --> 02:14:22.012
[JULIUS CHOKING]

2141
02:14:24.807 --> 02:14:26.934
- EXECUTIONER: [SOFTLY. IN ENGLISH] Shit.
- [FLOORBOARD CREAKING]

2142
02:14:32.856 --> 02:14:34.483
[JULIUS CHOKING]

2143
02:14:34.566 --> 02:14:35.734
[ROPE CREAKING]

2144
02:14:37.027 --> 02:14:38.320
- [BODY THUMPS]
- [ROPE CREAKS]

2145
02:14:57.339 --> 02:14:58.340
[SIGHS]

2146
02:15:01.927 --> 02:15:02.928
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

2147
02:15:18.944 --> 02:15:20.946
- [LEVER CLANKS]
- [GALLOW THUDS]

2148
02:15:33.834 --> 02:15:34.835
[SIGHS]

2149
02:15:37.338 --> 02:15:39.340
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

2150
02:15:42.468 --> 02:15:43.719
[SOFTLY] Son of a bitch.

2151
02:15:48.766 --> 02:15:49.850
He escaped.

2152
02:16:05.032 --> 02:16:06.575
RADIO GUEST: <i>I have to be honest.
Dr. Kelley.</i>

2153
02:16:06.658 --> 02:16:09.828
<i>I find some of the conclusions
in your book quite unbelievable.</i>

2154
02:16:10.662 --> 02:16:15.793
<i>You were dealing with the Nazis.
who you must admit are a unique people.</i>

2155
02:16:15.876 --> 02:16:17.378
DOUGLAS: <i>They are not a unique people.</i>

2156
02:16:17.461 --> 02:16:22.174
There are people like the Nazis
in every country in the world today.

2157
02:16:22.257 --> 02:16:24.760
RADIO GUEST: Not in America.
DOUGLAS: Yes. in America!

2158
02:16:25.677 --> 02:16:28.472
Their personality patterns
are not obscure.

2159
02:16:28.555 --> 02:16:31.100
They are people who want to be in power.

2160
02:16:31.183 --> 02:16:33.143
And while you say they don't exist here.

2161
02:16:33.227 --> 02:16:37.022
I would say I'm quite certain
there are people in America

2162
02:16:37.106 --> 02:16:41.110
who would willingly climb over the corpses
of half the American public

2163
02:16:41.193 --> 02:16:43.695
if they knew they could gain control
of the other half.

2164
02:16:43.779 --> 02:16:44.863
Doctor. please.

2165
02:16:44.947 --> 02:16:47.032
They stoke hatred.

2166
02:16:48.409 --> 02:16:50.577
It's what Hitler and Göring did.

2167
02:16:50.661 --> 02:16:52.538
- and it is textbook.
- [MICROPHONE FEEDBACK]

2168
02:16:53.372 --> 02:16:55.916
And if you think the next time it happens.

2169
02:16:55.999 --> 02:16:59.002
we're gonna recognize it because
they're wearing scary uniforms...

2170
02:16:59.086 --> 02:17:00.295
[CHAIR CREAKING]

2171
02:17:01.296 --> 02:17:03.090
...you're out of your damn mind.

2172
02:17:09.012 --> 02:17:11.306
More with our panel when we return.

2173
02:17:11.390 --> 02:17:12.724
- [SWITCH CLICKS]
- [DOUGLAS SIGHS]

2174
02:17:14.977 --> 02:17:16.728
Yeah. uh-huh. Uh...

2175
02:17:16.812 --> 02:17:19.273
They're not gonna invite you
to stay for the next segment.

2176
02:17:20.816 --> 02:17:21.817
Let's go.

2177
02:17:24.027 --> 02:17:25.279
DOUGLAS: Hmm.

2178
02:17:31.368 --> 02:17:32.578
And just so you know...

2179
02:17:34.288 --> 02:17:37.958
trashing our country is probably not
the best way to sell your book.

2180
02:17:40.377 --> 02:17:41.378
DOUGLAS: Hmm.

2181
02:17:46.925 --> 02:17:47.926
[SIGHS]

2182
02:17:48.010 --> 02:17:50.012
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

2183
02:18:57.454 --> 02:18:59.456
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

2184
02:20:58.950 --> 02:21:00.952
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

